'''亚裔美国人军事史'''最早可以追溯至[[1812年战争|1812年战争]]（第二次独立战争）时期，当时就有[[亚裔|亚裔]][[士兵|士兵]]加入[[美国军队|美国军队]]与[[英国军队|英国军队]]作战<ref name="AFPS">{{cite news |first=Rudi |last=Williams |title=DoD's Personnel Chief Gives Asian-Pacific American History Lesson |url=http://archive.defense.gov/news/newsarticle.aspx?id=16498 |work=American Forces Press Service |publisher=U.S. Department of Defense |date=2005-06-03 |accessdate=2009-08-26 |archive-date=2015-09-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150925074648/http://archive.defense.gov/news/newsarticle.aspx?id=16498 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在后来的[[南北战争|南北战争]]期间，[[北軍|联邦军（北軍）]]和[[美利坚联盟国|邦联军（南軍）]]两方皆有亚裔军人参战的记录<ref name="AFPS" /><ref name="GN" /><ref name="CHCP" />。在此之后，亚裔美国人主要在[[美国海军|美国海军]]服役直到[[美菲战争|美菲战争]]<ref name="DEOMI">{{cite web |url=https://books.google.com/books/about/A_Review_of_Data_on_Asian_Americans.html?id=FQ3njwEACAAJ |title=A Review of Data on Asian Americans |author= |date=August 1998 |work=Defense Equal Opportunity Management Institute |publisher=Department of Defense |accessdate=2011-03-01 |archive-date=2019-05-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190513041646/https://books.google.com/books/about/A_Review_of_Data_on_Asian_Americans.html?id=FQ3njwEACAAJ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

到了20世纪初，亚裔美国人开始进入[[西点军校|西点军校]]等[[美国联邦军事院校|联邦軍事院校]]。同一时期，也产生了第一位获得代表美国最高[[军事荣誉|军事荣誉]]——[[荣誉勋章|荣誉勋章]]的亚裔美国军人<ref name="JBNMOH">{{cite web |accessdate = 2009-06-08 |url = http://www.history.army.mil/html/moh/philippine.html |title = United States Army Center of Military History Medal of Honor Citations Archive |work = American Medal of Honor recipients for the Philippine Insurrection |publisher = United States Army Center of Military History |date = 2009-06-08 |archive-date = 2008-04-20 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080420212952/http://www.history.army.mil/html/moh/philippine.html |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="1908WP" />。 [[第一次世界大战|第一次世界大战]]中，亚裔等非白人族群在国民军（National Army）中服役<ref name="WWIQ" />。一战以后，亚裔军人陷入默默无闻的低潮，直到[[第二次世界大战|第二次世界大战]]，涌现出诸多[[日裔美國人|日裔]]<ref name="PBSTheWarJA"/><ref name="JASWW2">{{cite journal |year=2012 |title=Nisei served in U.S. Army Air Corps, Navy, Coast Guard, Marine Corps, and Merchant Marines during World War II |author=James McIlwain |journal=JAVA Advocate |volume=XX |issue=3 |pages=7 |publisher=Japanese American Veterans Association |url=http://javadc.org/media/document/java-advocate/JAVA-Advocate-Fall-2012.pdf |accessdate=2013-01-21 |archive-date=2014-03-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140306094844/http://javadc.org/media/document/java-advocate/JAVA-Advocate-Fall-2012.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>、[[华裔美国人|华裔]]<ref name="OMC" />、[[海外菲律賓人|菲裔]]<ref name="FASWW2" />、[[韩裔美国人|韩裔]]<ref name="KASWW2" />等在战争中做出巨大贡献的亚裔美軍军人。

根据1948年[[杜鲁门|杜鲁门]][[总统|总统]]颁布的[[9981號行政命令|9981號行政命令]]废止了军队中的[[种族隔离|种族隔离]]制度，如[[美国陆军第442步兵团|陸軍442步兵团]]等一些由亚裔編成的部隊均取消編制，士兵分配至其他单位<ref name="NJ" />。在[[韩战|韩战]]和[[越战|越战]]中又出现了数位获得荣誉勋章的亚裔美国军人。此后，亚裔美国人继续在军队中服役，直至今日<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.army.mil/asianpacificsoldiers/moh/koreanwar.html |title=Korean War Recipients |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |work=Asian Pacific Americans in the United States Army |publisher=United States Army |accessdate=2013-01-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121015200841/http://www.army.mil/asianpacificsoldiers/moh/koreanwar.html |archivedate=2012-10-15 }}<br/>{{cite web |url=http://www.army.mil/asianpacificsoldiers/moh/vietnamwar.html |title=Vietnam War Recipients |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |work=Asian Pacific Americans in the United States Army |publisher=United States Army |accessdate=2013-01-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121015200953/http://www.army.mil/asianpacificsoldiers/moh/vietnamwar.html |archivedate=2012-10-15 }}</ref><ref name="AAS2009">{{cite web |url=http://www.ncdsv.org/images/ARMY_ArmyProfile_2009.pdf |title=FY09 Army Profile |author=Dr. Betty D. Maxfield |date=2009-09-30 |work=Headquarters, Department of the Army |publisher=United States Army |accessdate=2011-04-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101218012554/http://ncdsv.org/images/ARMY_ArmyProfile_2009.pdf |archivedate=2010-12-18 }}</ref>。
