1901年，美国陆军组建[[菲律賓保安部隊|菲律賓保安部隊]]<ref>{{cite book |title=Encyclopedia of United States Army Insignia and Uniforms |last=Emerson |first=William K. |year=1996 |publisher=University of Oklahoma Press |isbn=9780806126227 |page=295 |accessdate=2012-07-05 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=trbBXKeHO3sC&lpg=PA295&ots=a4Vp9xu1N7&dq=1901%20Philippine%20Constabulary%20History&pg=PA295#v=onepage&q=1901%20Philippine%20Constabulary%20History&f=false |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191837/http://books.google.com/books?id=trbBXKeHO3sC&lpg=PA295&ots=a4Vp9xu1N7&dq=1901%20Philippine%20Constabulary%20History&pg=PA295#v=onepage&q=1901%20Philippine%20Constabulary%20History&f=false |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite web |url=http://hss.pnp.gov.ph/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=34:history-of-camp-crame&catid=27:history&Itemid=32 |title=History of Camp Crame |date=2010-08-25 |work=Headquarters Support Service |publisher=Philippine National Police |accessdate=2012-07-05 |quote=With the official designation and consumption of General Henry T Allen as its first Chief, the Constabulary was formally inaugurated in August 8, 1901 at Intramuros and with the bulk of   its organization housed at the Gagalangin Barracks in Manila. }}{{dead link|date=2018年2月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>和{{Link-en|菲律宾侦查军|Philippine Scouts}}<ref>{{cite web |last=Olson |first=John E. |title=The History of the Philippine Scouts |url=http://www.philippine-scouts.org/history/history-of-the-scouts.html |date=2007-05-11 |work=History |publisher=Philippine Scouts Heritage Society |accessdate=2009-08-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090725103934/http://www.philippine-scouts.org/history/history-of-the-scouts.html |archive-date=2009-07-25 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>两支菲裔战斗部队作为进攻[[菲律宾第一共和国|菲律宾第一共和国]]的武装力量的组成部分，并在[[美屬菲律賓|占领菲律宾]]后负责镇压叛乱。同年，[[威廉·麦金莱|麦金莱]]总统发布行政命令允许美国海军招收500名菲律宾士兵<ref>{{cite web |first=J.S. |last=Hooker |title=Filipinos in the United States Navy |url=https://www.history.navy.mil/research/library/online-reading-room/title-list-alphabetically/f/filipinos-in-the-united-states-navy.html |date=October 1976 |work=Naval Historical Center |publisher=Department of the Navy |accessdate=2009-09-02 |archive-date=2006-08-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060820202543/http://www.history.navy.mil/library/online/filipinos.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在这中间，就包括了第一位获得荣誉勋章的亚裔军人——二等兵{{link-en|何塞·尼斯佩洛斯|José B. Nísperos}}。他是一名菲律宾侦查军成员，在莫罗暴乱中保护了他的同僚们，因此在1911年获颁荣誉勋章<ref name="JBNMOH" />。 1915年，海军士兵{{link-en|特雷斯弗罗·特立尼达|Telesforo Trinidad}}和他的长官{{link-en|罗伯特·凯里|Robert Webster Cary}}少尉因在圣地亚哥号战列舰的锅炉发生爆炸后拯救同僚们的英勇行为獲授荣誉勋章<ref>{{cite web |last=George J. |first=Albert |title=The U.S.S. San Diego and the California Naval Militia |url=http://www.militarymuseum.org/USSSanDiego.html |date= |work=The California State Military Museum |publisher=California State Military Department |accessdate=2009-09-22 |archive-date=2012-04-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120402145751/http://www.militarymuseum.org/USSSanDiego.html |dead-url=no }} and<br/>{{cite web |title=Medal of Honor RecipientsInterim Awards, 1915–1916 |url=http://www.history.army.mil/html/moh/interim1915-16.html |date=2009-08-03 |work=Center of Military History |publisher=United States Army |accessdate=2009-09-22 |archive-date=2009-06-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090623025425/http://www.history.army.mil/html/moh/interim1915-16.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。目前为止，特立尼达仍是唯一一位获得海军荣誉勋章的亚裔军人<ref>{{cite news |title=Pinoy WWII vets still top Fil-Am concern |author=Rodney Jaleco |url=http://news.abs-cbn.com/global-filipino/10/19/10/pinoy-wwii-vets-still-top-fil-am-concern |newspaper=ABS-CBN |date=2010-10-19 |accessdate=2011-01-16 |archive-date=2016-01-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160109144800/http://news.abs-cbn.com/global-filipino/10/19/10/pinoy-wwii-vets-still-top-fil-am-concern |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite web |url=http://www.deomi.org/downloadableFiles/ap98.pdf |title=Asian and Pacific Island American Heritage |author= |year=1998 |work= |publisher=Defense Equal Opportunity Management Institute |accessdate=2011-03-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110725230207/http://www.deomi.org/downloadableFiles/ap98.pdf |archivedate=2011-07-25 }}</ref>。

====早期的亚裔军校学员====
在1860年代晚期就有[[亚洲人|亚洲人]]錄取進入[[美国海军学院|美国海军学院]]，出身该校1873年班的日本留学生，后为[[华族_(日本)|华族]]的{{link-ja|松村淳藏|松村淳蔵}}[[男爵|男爵]]是该校第一位亚洲毕业生<ref name="SCA">{{cite book |title=Sea change at Annapolis: the United States Naval Academy, 1949–2000, Volume 415 |last=Gelfand |first=H. Michael |year=2006 |publisher=UNC Press |isbn=9780807830475 |page=48 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=dJDHptZWHUUC&lpg=PA48&ots=KTHcc3pCFW&dq=first%20filipino%20graduate%20usna&pg=PA48#v=onepage&q=first%20filipino%20graduate%20usna&f=false |accessdate=2009-09-02 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627192545/http://books.google.com/books?id=dJDHptZWHUUC&lpg=PA48&ots=KTHcc3pCFW&dq=first%20filipino%20graduate%20usna&pg=PA48#v=onepage&q=first%20filipino%20graduate%20usna&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Japan encounters the barbarian: Japanese travellers in America and Europe |last=Beasley |first=William |year=1995 |publisher=Yale University Press |isbn=9780300063240 |page=135 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=X8qI7vtqcMEC&lpg=PA134&ots=pg_-HVu5jR&dq=%22Matsumura%20Junzo%22&pg=PA135#v=onepage&q=Annapolis&f=false |accessdate=2009-09-02 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627192527/http://books.google.com/books?id=X8qI7vtqcMEC&lpg=PA134&ots=pg_-HVu5jR&dq=%22Matsumura%20Junzo%22&pg=PA135#v=onepage&q=Annapolis&f=false |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite book |title=The Mikado's Empire |last=Griffis |first=William Elliot |year=1876 |publisher=Harper |location=New York |isbn= |page=8 |url=http://www.archive.org/stream/themikadosempire00grifiala/themikadosempire00grifiala_djvu.txt |accessdate=2009-09-02 }}</ref>。作为外国人的松村和多数来美国的留学生一样，毕业后选择回到自己的国家服役<ref name="SCA" />。大约四十年以后，第一批亚裔才追隨亚洲人前輩进入了美国联邦级别的军事院校。出身美属菲律宾的华裔学员{{link-en|文森特·林|Vicente Lim}}就是他们中的一员。林是西点军校1914届毕业生，毕业后在菲律宾侦查军中担任少尉<ref name="1908WP">{{cite book |title=Annual report of the Secretary of War |authorlink=United States War Department |year=1915 |publisher=U.S. Government Printing Office |location=Washington |isbn= |page=11 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=To0sAAAAIAAJ&lpg=PP25&ots=sjqTjAlLeQ&dq=1910%20Filipino%20West%20Point&pg=PP25#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2011-04-27 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191919/http://books.google.com/books?id=To0sAAAAIAAJ&lpg=PP25&ots=sjqTjAlLeQ&dq=1910%20Filipino%20West%20Point&pg=PP25#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=The Philippine revolution of 1896: ordinary lives in extraordinary times |last=García |first=Florentino Rodao |coauthors=Florentino Rodao, Felice Noelle Rodríguez |year=2001 |publisher=Ateneo de Manila University Press |isbn=9789715503860 |page=110 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=l533SkJ2VCkC&lpg=PA110&ots=2i96UKWLMm&dq=Vicente%20Lim%20%22west%20point%22&pg=PA110#v=onepage&q=Vicente%20Lim%20%22west%20point%22&f=false |accessdate=2009-09-02 |archive-date=2011-07-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722091133/http://books.google.com/books?id=l533SkJ2VCkC&lpg=PA110&ots=2i96UKWLMm&dq=Vicente%20Lim%20%22west%20point%22&pg=PA110#v=onepage&q=Vicente%20Lim%20%22west%20point%22&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。他是第一位少数錄取進入西点军校的[[美屬菲律賓|美属菲律宾]]人，在当时一个班里只能有1位菲律宾人，且最多只能有4人<ref name="1908WP" /><ref>{{cite book |title=The World almanac and book of facts |year=1914 |publisher=Newspaper Enterprise Association |isbn= |page=423 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=-GQ3AAAAMAAJ&lpg=PA423&ots=FXWVLKddwm&dq=1910%20Filipino%20West%20Point&pg=PA423#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2011-04-27 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627192559/http://books.google.com/books?id=-GQ3AAAAMAAJ&lpg=PA423&ots=FXWVLKddwm&dq=1910%20Filipino%20West%20Point&pg=PA423#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。从1916年起，美国海军学院也开始招收美属菲律宾人，第一批军校生在1919年入校学习<ref name="SCA"/>。这些毕业生在1935年[[菲律賓自治領|菲律宾自治]]时失去了美国国民（United States nationals）之身份，他们中的许多人选择在菲律宾军中继续服役<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chanrobles.com/tydingsmcduffieact.htm |title=The Philippine Independence Act (Tydings-McDuffie Act) |author= |date= |work=Philippine laws, statutes and codes |publisher=Chan Robles Virtual Law Library |accessdate=2012-07-08 |quote=For the purposes of the Immigration Act of 1917, the Immigration Act of 1924 [except section 13 (c)], this section, and all other laws of the United States relating to the immigration, exclusion, or expulsion of aliens, citizens of the Philippine Islands who are not citizens of the United States shall be considered as if they were aliens. For such purposes the Philippine Islands shall be considered as a separate country and shall have for each fiscal year a quota of fifty. |archive-date=2011-06-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110611111931/http://www.chanrobles.com/tydingsmcduffieact.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>

====美墨边境战争====
[[File:General_Pershing_and_General_Bliss_inspecting_the_camp.jpg|thumb]]]]
二十世纪初，当其他国家沉浸在[[第一次世界大战|第一次世界大战]]的硝烟弥漫中时，美国把眼光投向了自己在南边的邻居——[[墨西哥|墨西哥]]。从1910年起，墨西哥卷入了长达十年的[[墨西哥革命|内战]]。1916年，当时割据墨国北方的枭雄[[龐丘·維拉|庞丘·维拉]]袭击了美国边境城镇[[哥伦布_(新墨西哥州)|哥伦布]]，杀死18名美国人，其中包括10名平民<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nps.gov/history/nr/travel/american_latino_heritage/Village_of_Columbus_and_Camp_Furlong.html |title=Village of Columbus and Camp Furlong Columbus, New Mexico |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |work=National Park Service |publisher=United States Department of the Interior |accessdate=2012-12-31 |archive-date=2012-12-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121230123008/http://www.nps.gov/history/nr/travel/american_latino_heritage/Village_of_Columbus_and_Camp_Furlong.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，引发了美墨边境战争，担任美军统帅的是[[约翰·潘兴|潘兴]]少将<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.history.army.mil/html/reference/army_flag/mexex.html |title=Mexican Expedition |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2010-11-19 |work=United States Army Center of Military History |publisher=United States Army |accessdate=2012-12-31 |archive-date=2017-12-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171229163110/https://history.army.mil/html/reference/army_flag/mexex.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。当时，有为数不少的墨西哥华人冒着被庞丘·维拉处以绞刑的危险选择在战争中协助美军直到1917年战争结束。战争结束后，尽管当时美国政府执行[[排华法案|排华法案]]，但潘兴等人通过游说[[美国国会|国会]]获得特别许可，将总共527位华人带回美国重新安置，他们大多数定居在[[圣安东尼奥_(得克萨斯州)|圣安东尼奥]]，后世称之“潘兴华人”（Pershing's Chinese）<ref>{{cite book |title=Mexico and the United States |last=Stacy |first=Lee |year=2002 |publisher=Marshall Cavendish |location=0761474021 |isbn=0-7614-7402-1 |page=182 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=DSzyMGh8pNwC&lpg=PA182&dq=chinese&pg=PA182#v=onepage&q=chinese&f=false |accessdate=2009-09-02 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627192133/http://books.google.com/books?id=DSzyMGh8pNwC&lpg=PA182&dq=chinese&pg=PA182#v=onepage&q=chinese&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

====第一次世界大战====
{{See also|第一次世界大战}}
1917年4月6日，美国加入[[协约国|协约国]]一方对[[德意志帝国|德意志帝国]]宣战，正式介入第一次世界大战<ref>{{cite web |url=https://history.state.gov/milestones/1914-1920/wwi |title=American Entry into World War I, 1917 |author=Office of the Historian |work=Bureau of Public Affairs |publisher=United States Department of State |accessdate=2012-12-31 |archive-date=2014-01-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140113004816/http://history.state.gov/milestones/1914-1920/wwi |dead-url=no }}</ref>。当时的美属菲律宾成立了国民警卫队响应宣战，但并未出现在实战之中<ref>{{cite book |last=Wilson |first=John B. |title=Maneuver and Firepower: The Evolution of Divisions and Separate Brigades |series=Army Lineage Series |chapter=The Test – World War I |url=http://www.history.army.mil/html/books/060/60-14-1/cmhPub_60-14-1.pdf |accessdate=2012-12-31 |year=1998 |publisher=United States Army Center of Military History |location=Washington, D.C. |isbn=9780160495717 |page=66 |archive-date=2014-03-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140301211444/http://www.history.army.mil/html/books/060/60-14-1/cmhPub_60-14-1.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。部队于1918年解散<ref>{{cite book |last=Rinaldi |first=Richard A. |title=The US Army in World War I: Orders of Battle |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=vsoh_fBkAtwC&lpg=PA73&ots=2wbGNrIMpn&dq=%22Philippine%20National%20Guard%22%20World%20War%20One&pg=PA73#v=onepage&q=%22Philippine%20National%20Guard%22%20World%20War%20One&f=false |accessdate=2012-12-31 |year=2004 |publisher=Tiger Lily Publications LLC |isbn=9780972029643 |page=73 |archive-date=2016-01-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160129072841/https://books.google.com/books?id=vsoh_fBkAtwC&lpg=PA73&ots=2wbGNrIMpn&dq=%22Philippine%20National%20Guard%22%20World%20War%20One&pg=PA73#v=onepage&q=%22Philippine%20National%20Guard%22%20World%20War%20One&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在美国国内，曾有一项计划征召[[拉丁裔美国人|拉美裔]]、[[美洲原住民|原住民]]和亚裔来填补国民军中的白人兵额，尽管他们中的大多数并未出现在实战之中<ref name="WWIQ">{{cite web |last=Allerfeldt |first=Kristofer |title=Work or Fight! |url=http://www.history.ac.uk/reviews/paper/allerfeldtk.html |date=January 2009 |work=Reviews in History |publisher=The Institute of Historical Research |accessdate=2013-02-04 |quote=He shows that while the Dawes Act and Alien Land Laws explicitly barred non-whites – Native Americans and Asians rather than ‘coloreds’ (African Americans) – from the ownership of land, the San Diego draft still included ‘American Indians, Japanese Americans, Chinese Americans and Mexican Americans’, all called as part of the ‘“white” quota’. Perhaps  unsurprisingly none of these groups ever saw combat, but at least for the Native Americans it contributed to their gaining of citizenship, en masse, in 1924. |archive-date=2012-08-03 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120803031110/http://www.history.ac.uk/reviews/paper/allerfeldtk.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref>，但也有少数人参与到实战当中，这里面包括了二等兵托马斯·克劳迪奥（Tomas Mateo Claudio），他是[[內華達大學雷諾分校|内华达大学]]的学生，也是第一位和唯一一位阵亡的菲裔美国军人。他在1918年阵亡于[[蒂耶里堡|蒂耶里堡]]之战<ref>{{citation |url=http://asianjournalusa.com/default.asp?sourceid=&smenu=141&twindow=&mad=&sdetail=3692&wpage=1&skeyword=&sidate=&ccat=&ccatm=&restate=&restatus=&reoption=&retype=&repmin=&repmax=&rebed=&rebath=&subname=&pform=&sc=1028&hn=asianjournalusa&he=.com |title=America's Thanksgiving and the Philippines' National Heroes Day: Two Holidays Rooted in History and Tradition |author=Zena Sultana-Babao |publisher=Asian Journal |accessdate=2008-01-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090111063105/http://asianjournalusa.com/default.asp?sourceid=&smenu=141&twindow=&mad=&sdetail=3692&wpage=1&skeyword=&sidate=&ccat=&ccatm=&restate=&restatus=&reoption=&retype=&repmin=&repmax=&rebed=&rebath=&subname=&pform=&sc=1028&hn=asianjournalusa&he=.com |archive-date=2009-01-11 |dead-url=yes }}<br/>{{cite news |title=Balitang Beterano: Facts about the Philippine independence |author=Sol Jose Vanzi |newspaper=Philippine Headline News Online |date=2004-06-03 |url=http://www.newsflash.org/2004/02/tl/tl012375.htm |accessdate=16OCT09 |archive-date=2012-06-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120609104852/http://www.newsflash.org/2004/02/tl/tl012375.htm |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite web |url=http://www.mb.com.ph/issues/2007/01/25/SCAU2007012585502.html |title=Schools, colleges and Universities: Tomas Claudio Memorial College |publisher=Manila Bulletin Online |accessdate=2007-07-04 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070707015924/http://www.mb.com.ph/issues/2007/01/25/SCAU2007012585502.html |archivedate=2007-07-07 |deadurl=yes }}<br/>- {{cite web |url=http://www.tcmc.edu.ph/ |title=Thomas Claudio Memorial College |publisher=www.tcmc.edu.ph |accessdate=2007-07-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070630115212/http://www.tcmc.edu.ph/ |archivedate=2007-06-30 }}</ref>。二等兵亨利·陈（Henry Chinn）则阵亡于阿尔贡森林<ref>{{cite book |title=Five Days in October: The Lost Battalion of World War I |last=Ferrell |first=Robert H. |year=2005 |publisher=University of Missouri Press |isbn=9780826215949 |page=97 |accessdate=2012-08-26 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=OhJPW4b8WmQC&lpg=PA97&ots=deRFCV4oA8&dq=Henry%20Chinn%20Lost%20Battalion&pg=PA97#v=onepage&q=Henry%20Chinn%20Lost%20Battalion&f=false |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627192100/http://books.google.com/books?id=OhJPW4b8WmQC&lpg=PA97&ots=deRFCV4oA8&dq=Henry%20Chinn%20Lost%20Battalion&pg=PA97#v=onepage&q=Henry%20Chinn%20Lost%20Battalion&f=false |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite book |title=The Lost Battalion |last=Johnson |first=Thomas M. |last2=Pratt |first2=Fletcher |others=Edward M. Coffman |year=2000 |publisher=University of Nebraska Press |isbn=9780803276130 |page=228 |accessdate=2012-08-26 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=vB8SU4cZ4VMC&lpg=PA220&ots=b7hI22ZC4e&dq=Chinn%20Lost%20Battalion&pg=PA220#v=onepage&q=Chinn%20Lost%20Battalion&f=false |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627192611/http://books.google.com/books?id=vB8SU4cZ4VMC&lpg=PA220&ots=b7hI22ZC4e&dq=Chinn%20Lost%20Battalion&pg=PA220#v=onepage&q=Chinn%20Lost%20Battalion&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>，一位叫做兴（Sing Kee）的华裔士官在该系列战役中获得了美国陆军第二高榮銜——[[杰出服役十字勋章_(美国)|杰出服役十字勋章]]，一战中著名的電影《[[迷路的大軍_(2001年)|迷路的大军]]》（''The Lost Battalion''）便有劇情是取材於该阶段的战斗<ref>{{cite book |title=Lost Battalions: The Great War and the Crisis of American Nationality |last=Slotkin |first=Richard |year=2006 |publisher=Macmillan |isbn=9780805081381 |page=199 |accessdate=2012-08-26 |url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Lost_Battalions.html?id=untfy7pCwWgC |quote=Sing Kee would reeive the Distinguished Service Cross and be promoted to color sergeant, the highest rank attained by a Chinese-American in the AEF. |archive-date=2016-10-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161014231823/https://books.google.com/books/about/Lost_Battalions.html?id=untfy7pCwWgC |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite web |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dJt5AAAAMAAJ&pg=PA119&lpg=PA119&dq=Quarantine+And+Its+Aftereffects&source=bl&ots=LYFd4_vnD8&sig=h6MCv_-RuGaJopLPwM58Cf_KqrQ&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiqo_WE9d7UAhUl6IMKHRYVDZwQ6AEIKDAA#v=onepage&q=Quarantine%20And%20Its%20Aftereffects&f=false |title=Quarantine And Its Aftereffects |author=Nancy Wey |date=2004-11-17 |work=Five Views: An Ethnic Historic Site Survey for California |publisher=National Park Service |accessdate=2013-02-26 |quote=On June 13, 1919, Sing Kee returned home to San Jose after receiving the Distinguished Service Cross for bravery in action with the 77th or "Liberty" Division in the Argonne Forest. |archive-date=2019-05-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190513123034/https://books.google.com/books?id=dJt5AAAAMAAJ&pg=PA119&lpg=PA119&dq=Quarantine+And+Its+Aftereffects&source=bl&ots=LYFd4_vnD8&sig=h6MCv_-RuGaJopLPwM58Cf_KqrQ&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiqo_WE9d7UAhUl6IMKHRYVDZwQ6AEIKDAA#v=onepage&q=Quarantine%20And%20Its%20Aftereffects&f=false |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite web |url=http://militarytimes.com/citations-medals-awards/recipient.php?recipientid=12842 |title=Valor awards for Sing Kee |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |work=Military Times Hall of Valor |publisher=Gannett Government Media Corporation |accessdate=2013-02-26 |archive-date=2014-02-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221183516/http://www.militarytimes.com/citations-medals-awards/recipient.php?recipientid=12842 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。还有一位名叫西村德太郎（Tokutaro Nishimura Slocum）的日裔军士长在[[第82空降师|82步兵师]]第328步兵团服役<ref name="Slocum">{{cite journal |last=Salyer |first=Lucy |date=December 2004 |title=Baptism by Fire: Race, Military Service, and U.S. Citizenship Policy, 1918–1935 |journal=The Journal of American History |volume=91 |issue=3 |url=http://www.oahsecure.org/portal/publications/pub:jah/volume:91/number:3/starting_page:847/pt:pub |accessdate=2013-02-04 }}</ref>。在海军方面，战争结束时仅菲裔士兵就有不少于5700人<ref>{{cite book |title=The blood of government: race, empire, the United States, & the Philippines |last=Kramer |first=Paul Alexander |year=2006 |publisher=UNC Press |isbn=978-0-8078-5653-6 |page=384 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=e2OIAj3cp7wC&lpg=PA384&ots=u3vDK9_r_6&dq=all%20filipino%20crew%20united%20states%20navy&pg=PA384#v=onepage&q=all%20filipino%20crew%20united%20states%20navy&f=false |accessdate=2009-11-22 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627192119/http://books.google.com/books?id=e2OIAj3cp7wC&lpg=PA384&ots=u3vDK9_r_6&dq=all%20filipino%20crew%20united%20states%20navy&pg=PA384#v=onepage&q=all%20filipino%20crew%20united%20states%20navy&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。总的来说，在一战中，数以千计的华裔、日裔、韩裔、[[越裔美国人|越裔]]和菲裔加入了美军<ref>{{cite book |editor1-first=James C. |editor1-last=Bradford |title=A Companion to American Military History: 2 Volume Set |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=6TctrNS2-34C&lpg=PA194&vq=Asian&pg=PA887#v=snippet&q=Asian&f=false |accessdate=2013-02-09 |series=Volume 45 of Blackwell Companions to American History |year=2009 |publisher=John Wiley & Sons |isbn=1444315110 |chapter=Minorities in the Military |last1=Bruscino, Jr. |first1=Thomas A. |page=887 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627192534/http://books.google.com/books?id=6TctrNS2-34C&lpg=PA194&vq=Asian&pg=PA887#v=snippet&q=Asian&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>，他们在战后冲破重重法律阻隔，獲准成为归化[[美国公民|美国公民]]<ref>{{cite web |title=World War I |url=http://www.army.mil/asianpacificsoldiers/history/worldwar1.html |work=Asian Pacific Americans |publisher=United States Army |accessdate=2009-09-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090809082539/http://www.army.mil/asianpacificsoldiers/history/worldwar1.html |archivedate=2009-08-09 }}<br/>{{cite book |title= Asian Americans: An Interpretive History |series= Twayne's immigrant heritage of America series |last= Chan |first= Sucheng |year= 1991 |publisher= Twayne |isbn= 978-0-8057-8437-4 |page= 196 |url= http://books.google.com/books?ei=PxBuTcKmK4O0sAPb3cS2Cw&ct=result&id=P9Zro9x6mZQC&dq=Asian+Americans,+an+Interpretive+History&q=citizen+world+war#search_anchor |accessdate= 2011-03-02 |archive-date= 2014-06-27 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191846/http://books.google.com/books?ei=PxBuTcKmK4O0sAPb3cS2Cw&ct=result&id=P9Zro9x6mZQC&dq=Asian+Americans,+an+Interpretive+History&q=citizen+world+war#search_anchor |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref name="Slocum"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pbs.org/rootsinthesand/i_bhagat1.html |title=Bhagat Singh Thind |author= |year=2000 |work= |publisher=Public Broadcasting System |accessdate=2009-11-28 |archive-date=2009-04-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090411091112/http://www.pbs.org/rootsinthesand/i_bhagat1.html |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite web |url=http://www.janm.org/nrc/militarych.php |title=Japanese Americans in America's Wars: A Chronology |publisher=Japanese American National Museum |accessdate=2009-11-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100613010440/http://www.janm.org/nrc/militarych.php |archivedate=2010-06-13 }}</ref>。

====战间期====
[[File:Marines_teach_Filipino_cadets.jpg|thumb]]]]
在[[战间期|战间期]]，美军参与了几次小规模的军事行动，包括参与[[协约国武装干涉俄国内战|协约国武装干涉俄国内战]]、对中北美及加勒比海地区用兵的[[香蕉戰爭|香蕉战争]]，此外美国长达近百年的{{link-en|扬子江巡航|Yangtze Patrol}}也直接或间接受到[[抗日战争|日本侵华]]的波及。在1918年至1933年间，至少3900名菲裔士兵在美国海军中服役，从事炊事兵的工作，替代了原岗位中一大部分[[非裔美国人|黑人]]炊事兵<ref>{{Cite report |title=The Filipino American Community |url=http://www.azhistory.net/aahps/f_filipino_etc.pdf |last=Solliday |first=Scott |coauthors=Vince Murray |year=2007 |publisher=City of Phoenix |accessdate=2011-03-10 |date= |archive-date=2011-07-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723021726/http://www.azhistory.net/aahps/f_filipino_etc.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。直到一战爆发，才准許菲裔海军士兵从事其他军职，然而在一战之后又限制了菲裔从事军官侍从和厨师的工作<ref>{{cite book |title=Home Bound: Filipino American Lives across Cultures, Communities, and Countries |first=Yen |last=Le Espiritu |publisher=University of California Press |year=2003 |isbn=9780520235274 |page=29 |accessdate=2012-10-23 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=W19b7W7nsxYC&lpg=PA30&ots=MR8vPoxhBs&dq=Navy%20Bases%20Filipino%20communities&pg=PA29#v=onepage&q=Navy%20Bases%20Filipino%20communities&f=false |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627192025/http://books.google.com/books?id=W19b7W7nsxYC&lpg=PA30&ots=MR8vPoxhBs&dq=Navy%20Bases%20Filipino%20communities&pg=PA29#v=onepage&q=Navy%20Bases%20Filipino%20communities&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

1934年，[[钟云|钟云]]成为了第一位拥有[[美国公民|美国公民]]身份的亚裔海军学院毕业生<ref name="SCA"/>，第一位拥有美国公民身份的亚裔西点军校毕业生则为洪荣福（Wing Fook Jung），他毕业于1940年<ref>{{cite web |last=Graham |first=Sylvia |title=Firsts & Lasts at USMA |url=http://1972e3usma.org/files/Firsts_and_Lasts_at_USMA.pdf |year=2005 |work=Register of Graduates and Former Cadets |publisher=United States Military Academy |accessdate=2009-09-24 |archive-date=2016-04-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160421125107/http://1972e3usma.org/files/Firsts_and_Lasts_at_USMA.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在1940年代，日裔是數量最龐大的亚裔美国人族群，其餘依次为华裔、菲裔、[[印度裔美國人|印度裔]]和韩裔<ref>{{cite web |last=Truesdell |first=Leon |title=Population, Characteristics of the nonwhite population by race |url=http://www2.census.gov/prod2/decennial/documents/41271189.pdf |year=1943 |work=Sixteenth Census of the United States:1940 |publisher=United States Department of Commerce |accessdate=2009-09-21 |archive-date=2010-08-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100810033619/http://www2.census.gov/prod2/decennial/documents/41271189.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

1939年9月，[[波兰战役|德国入侵波兰]]打破了欧洲的宁静<ref>{{cite news |title=1939: Germany invades Poland |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/onthisday/hi/dates/stories/september/1/newsid_3506000/3506335.stm |newspaper=BBC News |year=2008 |accessdate=2013-02-04 |archive-date=2008-04-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080406132000/http://news.bbc.co.uk/onthisday/hi/dates/stories/september/1/newsid_3506000/3506335.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。当时美国尚且对此保持中立，但是美国人在宣战前还是在某种程度上参与到了战争当中，比如援华的[[飞虎队|飞虎队]]和[[英国皇家空军|英国皇家空军]]的{{link-en|雄鷹中隊|Eagle Squadrons}}<ref>{{cite book |last=Ayling |first=Keith |title=They Fly for Victory |year=1943 |publisher=T. Nelson and sons |page=119 }}</ref>。美军还根据「现购自运」（cash and carry）政策向他国提供后勤支援，并承诺在大西洋上给以护航<ref>{{cite book |last=Potter |first=Elmer Belmont |last2=Adams |first2=Henry Hitch |title=Sea Power: A Naval History |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=zql2rWh6QAsC&lpg=PA255&ots=uzanG0fMUM&dq=%22Cash%20and%20carry%22%20escort%20convoy&pg=PA255#v=onepage&q=%22Cash%20and%20carry%22%20escort%20convoy&f=false |accessdate=2013-02-04 |year=1981 |publisher=Naval Institute Press |isbn=9780870216077 |page=255 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627192217/http://books.google.com/books?id=zql2rWh6QAsC&lpg=PA255&ots=uzanG0fMUM&dq=%22Cash%20and%20carry%22%20escort%20convoy&pg=PA255#v=onepage&q=%22Cash%20and%20carry%22%20escort%20convoy&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。1941年末，[[大日本帝国|日本]]对[[珍珠港|珍珠港]]的袭击，美国正式对[[轴心国|轴心国]]宣战<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/onthisday/hi/dates/stories/december/7/newsid_3494000/3494108.stm |title=1941: Japanese planes bomb Pearl Harbor |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |work=On this Day |publisher=BBC News |accessdate=2012-12-31 |archive-date=2012-08-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120821084636/http://news.bbc.co.uk/onthisday/hi/dates/stories/december/7/newsid_3494000/3494108.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。从那时起，亚裔美国人便参与到了这场战斗中来。包括日裔在内的许多亚裔美国人，在[[夏威夷|夏威夷]]前线[[瓦胡岛|瓦胡岛]]等地，对美军给以援助<ref name="Inouye">{{cite book |title=Distinguished Asian Americans: a biographical dictionary |last=Kim |first=Hyung-chan |year=1999 |publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group |isbn=0-313-28902-6 |page=135 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=prhRl6DYXRMC&lpg=PA135&ots=E_5FueH6pX&dq=pearl%20harbor%20inouye%201971&pg=PA135#v=onepage&q=pearl%20harbor%20inouye%201971&f=false |accessdate=2009-09-13 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191946/http://books.google.com/books?id=prhRl6DYXRMC&lpg=PA135&ots=E_5FueH6pX&dq=pearl%20harbor%20inouye%201971&pg=PA135#v=onepage&q=pearl%20harbor%20inouye%201971&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在地球的另一端，菲律宾自治领也在美军的指挥下，开始针对日本的入侵进行防御<ref>{{cite web |title=Philippine Islands |url=http://www.history.army.mil/brochures/pi/pi.htm |date=2003-10-03 |work=Center of Military History |publisher=U.S. Army |accessdate=2009-09-20 |archive-date=2011-05-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110523005633/http://www.history.army.mil/brochures/pi/PI.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

