随着珍珠港遭到袭击，包含众多日裔军人的{{link-en|夏威夷国民警卫队|Hawaii Army National Guard}}转入现役，开始从事驻守沙滩、清理碎石、献血和帮助伤员等工作。但是三天之后，这些日裔士兵因为他们血统的缘故被缴械，尽管缴械后的次日，他们又獲准重新武装，但一种紧张和不安的情绪一直持续到1942年6月5日<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goforbroke.org/learn/history/military_units/100th.php |title=100th Infantry battalion |author= |date= |work=History |publisher=Go For Broke National Education Center |accessdate=2011-03-02 |archive-date=2016-03-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160319164515/http://www.goforbroke.org/learn/history/military_units/100th.php |dead-url=no }}</ref>。与此同时，1942年1月19日，在[[夏威夷大学|夏威夷大学]]{{link-en|美国陆军预备军官训练团|Army Reserve Officers' Training Corps|后备军官训练团}}受训的军校生们<ref>{{cite web |url=http://hirono.house.gov/news/documentsingle.aspx?DocumentID=267216 |title=Congresswoman Hirono Statement on Legislation Honoring "Go For Broke" Japanese-American WWII Veterans with the Congressional Gold Medal |last1=Hirin |first1=Mazie K. |work=Floor Statements |publisher=United States House of Representatives |accessdate=2012-12-31 |quote=in spite of these acts of loyalty and courage, the U.S. Army discharged all Nisei in the ROTC unit, changed their draft status to ineligible, and segregated all Japanese Americans in the military on the mainland out of their units. |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121221030128/http://hirono.house.gov/news/documentsingle.aspx?DocumentID=267216 |archivedate=2012-12-21 }}</ref>和在夏威夷国民警卫队服役的日裔军人<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hawaii.edu/news/article.php?aId=5093 |title=Seven posthumous degrees to be awarded at ROTC Commissioning Ceremony |last1=McKay |first1=Kevin |last2=Chang |first2=Diane |date=2012-05-09 |work=News release archive |publisher=The University of Hawaii System |accessdate=2012-12-31 |quote=In the hours following the bombing, all UH ROTC cadets were told to report to duty, forming the Hawai‘i Territorial Guard (HTG), which was assigned to guard military installations on O‘ahu.  A month later, members who were of Japanese ancestry were expelled from the HTG because of their ethnicity. |archive-date=2012-11-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121104075048/http://www.hawaii.edu/news/article.php?aId=5093 |dead-url=no }}</ref>强制退伍<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nisei.hawaii.edu/object/io_1206614061171.html |title=Home Frot |last1=Miho |first1=Katsugo |year=2006 |work=The Hawaii Nisei Project |publisher=University of Hawaii |accessdate=2012-12-31 |quote=On January 19, 1942, all men of Japanese ancestry in the Hawaii Territorial Guard are discharged. |archive-date=2013-11-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104223640/http://nisei.hawaii.edu/object/io_1206614061171.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。许多退伍的日裔军人于2月份组成了[[美国陆军工兵部队|美国陆军工兵部队]]的一个辅助机构——“{{Link-en|大學勝利志願團|Varsity Victory Volunteers}}”<ref>{{cite book |last=Robinson |first=Greg |title=A Tragedy of Democracy: Japanese Confinement in North America |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=2N7yKKbBKD4C&lpg=PA119&dq=Discharged%20Guardsmen%20Varsity%20Victory%20Volunteers&pg=PA119#v=onepage&q=Discharged%20Guardsmen%20Varsity%20Victory%20Volunteers&f=false |accessdate=2012-12-31 |year=2010 |publisher=Columbia University Press |isbn=9780231129237 |page=119 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627192117/http://books.google.com/books?id=2N7yKKbBKD4C&lpg=PA119&dq=Discharged%20Guardsmen%20Varsity%20Victory%20Volunteers&pg=PA119#v=onepage&q=Discharged%20Guardsmen%20Varsity%20Victory%20Volunteers&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。 1942年6月5日，1400名日裔夏威夷国民兵分發到奥克兰，上岸后，他们组建成{{link-en|美国陆军第100步兵营|100th Infantry Battalion (United States)|第100步兵营}}——一支后来在战斗中屡建功勋的日裔部队<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goforbroke.org/learn/history/timeline/index.php |title=Timeline |author= |date= |work=History |publisher=Go For Broke National Education Center |accessdate=2011-03-02 |archive-date=2016-03-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160318235923/http://www.goforbroke.org/learn/history/timeline/index.php |dead-url=no }}</ref>。随后，除了已从军的日裔人士之外，所有日裔平民全經政府认定为“敌對外国人”（enemy aliens），直到1943年这项政策才获得改变<ref name="PBSTheWarJA">{{cite web |url=http://www.pbs.org/thewar/at_war_democracy_japanese_american.htm |title=Fighting for Democracy: Japanese Americans |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=September 2007 |work=WETA |publisher=Public Broadcasting Service |accessdate=2013-02-05 |archive-date=2012-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121111081736/http://www.pbs.org/thewar/at_war_democracy_japanese_american.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

8个月之后，军方做出了成立全日裔团级军事单位的决定，这就是后来著名的[[美国陆军第442步兵团|第442步兵团]]。 一开始，整个过程进行缓慢，又过了四个月时间，第442步兵团才开始训练，再两个月之后，第100步兵营率先開赴欧洲战场<ref name="100442CMH" />。起初，驻欧盟军总司令[[艾森豪威尔|艾森豪威尔]]将军的参谋团否决任用日裔军人的提案，但最终由[[马克·克拉克|克拉克]][[中将|中将]]接收，编隶于第五集团军旗下<ref name="PBSTheWarJA"/>。当第442团还在美国训练之时，第100步兵营正在欧洲战场上蒙受重大损失，他们因此获得了“紫心营”（Purple Heart Battalion）的称号<ref>{{cite news |title=The "Go for Broke" Regiment Lives Duty, Honor, Country |author=Rudi Williams |url=http://archive.defense.gov/news/newsarticle.aspx?id=45180 |newspaper=American Forces Press Service |date=2000-05-25 |accessdate=2012-08-20 |archive-date=2015-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924034317/http://archive.defense.gov/news/newsarticle.aspx?id=45180 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。1944年6月26日，在442步兵团到达欧洲战场两星期后，军方将第100步兵营并入第442步兵团，但100步兵营的战士们希望能够保持该营现有番号，因此将第442步兵团下辖的原第1营替代。根据当时的政策，军中亦实行种族隔离，所以重组后的第442步兵团突显日裔特色<ref>{{cite web |last=Nakagawa |first=Martha |title=In Times of War |url=https://www.kcet.org/history-society/in-times-of-war |date= |work=Rights of Passage |publisher=Community Television of Southern California |accessdate=2009-09-20 |archive-date=2019-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190222033438/https://www.kcet.org/history-society/in-times-of-war |dead-url=no }}</ref>，而在此之前，第442步兵团的士兵来自美国本土的[[日裔美國人囚禁|日裔美国人集中营]]，军官则大多数为白人<ref>{{cite web |last=Pike |first=John |title=100th Battalion, 442nd Infantry |url=http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/agency/army/100-442in.htm |date=2005-05-23 |work=Military |publisher=GlobalSecurity.org |accessdate=2009-09-20 |archive-date=2008-09-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080911011150/http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/agency/army/100-442in.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。 该团在以后的作战中功勋卓著，成为欧洲战场中最功勳彪炳的部队之一<ref name="100442CMH">{{cite web |title=100th Battalion, 442d Infantry |url=http://www.history.army.mil/html/topics/apam/100bn_442inf.html |date=2009-08-03 |work=Center of Military History |publisher=U.S. Army |accessdate=2009-09-20 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100608195042/http://www.history.army.mil/html/topics/apam/100bn_442inf.html |archivedate=2010-06-08 }}</ref>，他们在[[意大利王國_(1861–1946)|意大利]]、[[维希法国|法国]]、[[纳粹德国|德国]]参与了多场军事行动， 其中包括了解放[[达豪集中营|达豪集中营]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Central Europe Campaign (552nd Field Artillery battalion) |url=http://www.goforbroke.org/learn/history/military_units/522nd.php |date= |work=History |publisher=Go For Broke National Education Center |accessdate=2009-09-20 |archive-date=2016-03-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160319184843/http://www.goforbroke.org/learn/history/military_units/522nd.php |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

此外，加入了美军情报部队的日裔军人在太平洋前线也做出了自己的贡献，他们帮助破译日军情报，并在战后赴[[同盟國軍事佔領日本|盟军接管的日本]]協助佔領工作<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.njahs.org/misnorcal/campaigns/campaigns_japan.htm |title=Occupied Japan |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |year=2003 |work=Campaigns of the Pacific |publisher=Military Intelligence Service Association of Northern California |accessdate=2013-02-04 |archive-date=2013-09-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130930001208/http://www.njahs.org/misnorcal/campaigns/campaigns_japan.htm |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite web |url=http://www.njahs.org/misnorcal/campaigns/campaigns.htm |title=Pacific Theater |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |year=2003 |work=Campaigns of the Pacific |publisher=Military Intelligence Service Association of Northern California |accessdate=2013-02-04 |archive-date=2013-09-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130930003320/http://www.njahs.org/misnorcal/campaigns/campaigns.htm |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite book |last=McNaughton |first=James C. |authorlink= |title=Nisei Linguists: Japanese Americans in the Military Intelligence Service during World War II |url=http://www.history.army.mil/html/books/nisei_linguists/CMH_70-99-1.pdf |accessdate=2013-02-08 |year=2007 |publisher=Center of Military History, United States Army |isbn=1780390432 |pages=514 |archive-date=2013-03-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130309022041/http://www.history.army.mil/html/books/nisei_linguists/CMH_70-99-1.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。第一位在情报单位服役的亚裔女性是通过加入陆军女性部队这一途径进入的<ref name="WomenWWII">{{cite web |url=http://archive.defense.gov/News/NewsArticle.aspx?ID=43027 |title=Asian Pacific American Women Served in World War II, Too |author=Rudi Williams |date=1999-05-27 |work=American Forces Press Service |publisher=United States Department of Defense |accessdate=2012-07-18 |archive-date=2015-09-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150905094823/http://archive.defense.gov/News/NewsArticle.aspx?ID=43027 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。还有一批来自第442步兵团的志愿者中选进入[[战略情报局|战略情报局]]，随后派往[[中缅印战区|中缅印战区]]工作，在那里，他们从事[[隐蔽行动|潜伏]]、翻译、审问和信号情报等活动<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cia.gov/news-information/featured-story-archive/2012-featured-story-archive/japanese-americans-WWII-intel.html |title=Japanese Americans in World War II Intelligence |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2012-05-11 |work=Featured Story Archive |publisher=Central Intelligence Agency |accessdate=2013-02-04 |archive-date=2013-02-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130220000218/https://www.cia.gov/news-information/featured-story-archive/2012-featured-story-archive/japanese-americans-WWII-intel.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。超过33000名日裔美国人在二战中参军<ref name="PBSTheWarJA"/>，当他们复员回家时，日裔军人发现社会上对他们的[[反日|偏见]]依然存在<ref name="PBSTheWarJA"/>。

1946年，第442团战士{{link-en|旨森贞雄|Sadao Munemori}}因其先前在意大利军事行动中的卓越表现而追授荣誉勋章，他是仅有两位陣亡後不久即獲追授荣誉勋章的亚裔军人之一，也是唯一的一位日裔<ref>{{cite web |url=http://valor.militarytimes.com/recipient.php?recipientid=2826 |title=Sadao S. Munemori |work=Military Times Hall of Valor |publisher=Gannett Government Media Corporation |accessdate=2012-10-30 |quote=Sadao Munemori was the ONLY Japanese-American awarded the Medal of Honor during or immediately after World War II. With prejudice still strong, it required intervention by Congress to at last see him posthumously awarded the Medal of Honor. }}</ref>。直到2000年，经过对前第442步兵团老兵功勋的重审后，增授21位日裔老兵荣誉勋章<ref>{{cite web |accessdate = 2009-08-25 |url = http://www.history.army.mil/html/moh/ap-moh1.html |title = Asian Pacific American World War II |work = Medal of Honor Recipients |publisher = United States Army Center of Military History |date = 2009-06-08 |archive-date = 2009-09-04 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090904054117/http://www.history.army.mil/html/moh/ap-moh1.html |dead-url = no }}</ref>。其中包括了原美国陆军上尉，时任[[美国参议院|国会参议员]]的[[丹尼尔·井上|丹尼尔·井上]]<ref name="Inouye"/>。2010年10月5日，国会制作了国会金质勋章（Congressional Gold Medal）用来表彰第442步兵团战斗部队和第100步兵营，还包括了二战时期在情报机构服役的6000名日裔老兵<ref name=steffen>{{citation |last=Steffen |first=Jordan |title=White House honors Japanese American WWII veterans |newspaper=The Los Angeles Times |date=2010-10-06 |url=http://www.latimes.com/news/nationworld/nation/la-na-veterans-medal-20101006,0,7017069.story |accessdate=2014-02-15 |archive-date=2010-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101007031655/http://www.latimes.com/news/nationworld/nation/la-na-veterans-medal-20101006%2C0%2C7017069.story |dead-url=no }}</ref>

=====华裔=====
{{See also|弗朗西斯·魏}}
[[File:Halftrack-fort-knox-4.jpg|right]]受训的华裔美军士兵]]
二战期间，大约有12000<ref>{{cite book |title=Americans first: Chinese Americans and the Second World War |last=Wong |first=Kevin Scott |year=2005 |publisher=Harvard University Press |isbn=978-0-674-01671-2 |page=1 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=wex-8MBRkKYC&lpg=PA50&ots=EBq45e5dhV&dq=%22Chinese%20Americans%22%20%22World%20War%20II%22&pg=PA1#v=onepage&q=%22Chinese%20Americans%22%20%22World%20War%20II%22&f=false |accessdate=2009-09-21 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627192603/http://books.google.com/books?id=wex-8MBRkKYC&lpg=PA50&ots=EBq45e5dhV&dq=%22Chinese%20Americans%22%20%22World%20War%20II%22&pg=PA1#v=onepage&q=%22Chinese%20Americans%22%20%22World%20War%20II%22&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>华裔在美军中服役，这约占当时全部华裔美国人口的22%<ref name="OMC">{{cite web |title=World War II/Post War Era |url=http://www.museumca.org/picturethis/4_7.html |work=Timeline |publisher=Oakland Museum of California |accessdate=2009-10-02 |archive-date=2010-06-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100620124044/http://museumca.org/picturethis/4_7.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，他们中的40%没有美国国籍<ref name="AFPS"/>。与日裔和菲裔不同，75%的华裔军人在非种族隔离的单位服役<ref name="AFPS"/>。华裔美国人将自己与日裔区分开来，因此遭受到较少的种族歧视<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.calisphere.universityofcalifornia.edu/calcultures/ethnic_groups/subtopic2c.html |title=Asian Americans:World War II |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |year=2013 |work=Calisphere |publisher=The Regents of The University of California |accessdate=2013-02-05 |archive-date=2013-04-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130404014155/http://www.calisphere.universityofcalifornia.edu/calcultures/ethnic_groups/subtopic2c.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。四分之一的华裔军人在[[美國陸軍航空軍|美国陆军航空军]]服役， 他们中的一些人調至[[中缅印战区|中缅印战区]]的第14空勤大隊（14th Air Service Group）<ref name="CACMH">{{cite web |author=James C. McNaughton |title=Chinese-Americans in World War II |url=http://www.history.army.mil/html/topics/apam/chinese-americans.html |work=Center of Military History |publisher=United States Army |date=2009-08-03 |accessdate=2009-10-02 |archive-date=2010-04-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100408143949/http://www.history.army.mil/html/topics/apam/chinese-americans.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>和[[中美混合團|中美混合團]]<ref name="page60"/>。剩下的约70%华裔军人分别在第3、4、6、32和77步兵师服役<ref name="OMC"/>。海军方面则在战前就开始招收华裔美国人入伍，但工作仅限于炊事兵<ref name="page60">{{cite book |title=Americans first: Chinese Americans and the Second World War |last=Wong |first=Kevin Scott |year=2005 |publisher=Harvard University Press |isbn=978-0-674-01671-2 |page=61 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=wex-8MBRkKYC&lpg=PA50&ots=EBq45e5dhV&dq=%22Chinese%20Americans%22%20%22World%20War%20II%22&pg=PA61#v=onepage&q=%22Chinese%20Americans%22%20%22World%20War%20II%22&f=false |accessdate=2009-10-02 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191509/http://books.google.com/books?id=wex-8MBRkKYC&lpg=PA50&ots=EBq45e5dhV&dq=%22Chinese%20Americans%22%20%22World%20War%20II%22&pg=PA61#v=onepage&q=%22Chinese%20Americans%22%20%22World%20War%20II%22&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>，直到1942年5月才停止这项限制<ref name="page60"/>。1943年，陆军女性部队开始招收华裔女性进入情报部门<ref name="WomenWWII" />。美国陆军航空军也开始招收华裔女性，其中的一小部分在后来以平民身份组成了女性航空军飞行员（Women Airforce Service Pilots）<ref name="WomenWWII" />。

1944年末，第34步兵团的[[弗朗西斯·魏|弗朗西斯·魏]]上尉因[[雷伊泰岛战役|雷伊泰岛之战]]追授杰出服役十字勋章，这项荣誉在2000年的重审中升格为荣誉勋章<ref name="CACMH"/>。威尔伯·施（Wilbur Carl Sze）则成为了第一位华裔海军陆战队军官<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.deomi.org/DownloadableFiles/humanRelations/documents/Asian_Pacific_American_Heritage_Month_Facts_of_the_Day.pdf |title=Asian Pacific American Heritage Month |author=Major Karen J. Gregory, USAFR |publisher=Defense Equal Opportunity Management Institute |accessdate=2011-05-31 |quote=On December 15, 1943, Wilbur Carl Sze was commissioned as a 2nd Lieutenant and the first Chinese-American officer in the U.S. Marine Corps |archive-date=2019-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190222033438/https://www.deomi.org/DownloadableFiles/humanRelations/documents/Asian_Pacific_American_Heritage_Month_Facts_of_the_Day.pdf |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite web |url=https://2001-2009.state.gov/r/pa/ei/pix/b/ocr/2002/10241.htm |title=apa-usmc02 |author= |year=2002 |work=Asian Pacific American Heritage Month 2002 |publisher=Department of Defense |accessdate=2011-05-31 |archive-date=2011-05-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110531143925/http://2001-2009.state.gov/r/pa/ei/pix/b/ocr/2002/10241.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=====菲裔=====
[[File:Propaganda_poster_depicts_the_Philippine_resistance_movement.jpg|thumb]]

菲律宾作为二战中亚洲战场的前线，在偷袭珍珠港后不久便遭到了日军攻击。当时镇守菲律宾自治领的统帅是[[麦克阿瑟|麦克阿瑟]]将军，他最初计划死守菲律宾<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.history.army.mil/books/70-7_06.htm |title=Chapter 6 |author=Louis Morton |date= |work=Center of Military History |publisher=United States Army |accessdate=2009-11-12 |archive-date=2010-01-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100109103729/http://www.history.army.mil/books/70-7_06.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>，但随着日军登陆[[吕宋|吕宋]]， 美军紧急启动[[橘色戰爭計畫|橘色戰爭計畫]]，匆忙退往[[巴丹半岛|巴丹半岛]]<ref>{{Citation | last =Merriam | first =Ray | year =1999 | title =War in the Philippines | publisher =Merriam Press | pages =98，70–82 | isbn =1-57638-164-1 | url =http://books.google.com/books?id=utbD8wwF91kC&pg=PA70&lpg=PA70&dq=26th+cavalry&source=web&ots=PGuA3JpiEt&sig=upw4pWSJRiZX7uT_ys6d-snEGss#PPA70,M1 | accessdate =2008-01-31 | archive-date =2014-06-27 | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191633/http://books.google.com/books?id=utbD8wwF91kC&pg=PA70&lpg=PA70&dq=26th+cavalry&source=web&ots=PGuA3JpiEt&sig=upw4pWSJRiZX7uT_ys6d-snEGss#PPA70,M1 | dead-url =no }}</ref>，以阻拒日军进驻[[馬尼拉灣|马尼拉湾]]<ref>{{cite book |chapter=The Decision To Withdraw to Bataan |chapterurl=http://www.history.army.mil/books/70-7_06.htm |last=Morton |first=Louis |title=Command Decisions |editor-first=Kent Roberts |editor-last=Greenfield |url=http://www.history.army.mil/books/70-7_0.htm |accessdate=2013-01-08 |year=2000 |publisher=Center of Military History, United States Army |location=Washington, D.C. |page=169 |lccn=59-60007 |archive-date=2009-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090305092003/http://www.history.army.mil/books/70-7_0.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。1942年3月，[[富兰克林·德拉诺·罗斯福|罗斯福总统]]将麦克阿瑟调离菲律宾<ref>{{cite book |editor1-first=Kent Roberts |editor1-last=Greenfield |last1=Morton |first1=Louis |title=The Fall of the Philippines |chapter=Command |chapterurl=http://www.history.army.mil/books/wwii/5-2/5-2_20.htm |accessdate=2012-01-08 |year=1953 |publisher=Center of Military History, United States Army |location=Washington, D.C. |lccn=53-63678 |page=357 |url=http://www.history.army.mil/books/wwii/5-2/5-2_Contents.htm |archive-date=2012-01-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120108061554/http://www.history.army.mil/books/wwii/5-2/5-2_Contents.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。同年4月，第二集团军司令官{{link-en|爱德华·金|Edward P. King}}少将因无法组织起有效的防御，向日军投降<ref>{{cite book |editor1-first=Kent Roberts |editor1-last=Greenfield |last1=Morton |first1=Louis |title=The Fall of the Philippines |chapter=Surrender |chapterurl=http://www.history.army.mil/books/wwii/5-2/5-2_26.htm |url=http://www.history.army.mil/books/wwii/5-2/5-2_Contents.htm |accessdate=2012-01-08 |year=1953 |publisher=Center of Military History, United States Army |location=Washington, D.C. |lccn=53-63678 |page=466 |archive-date=2012-01-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120108061554/http://www.history.army.mil/books/wwii/5-2/5-2_Contents.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>，75000名士兵成为战俘，其中63000人为菲律宾人<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.army.mil/asianpacificsoldiers/history/bataan.html |title=Bataan death March |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |work=Asian Pacific Americans in the United States Army |publisher=United States Army |accessdate=2013-01-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130331090851/http://www.army.mil/asianpacificsoldiers/history/bataan.html |archivedate=2013-03-31 }}</ref>，包括数千[[菲律宾华人|菲律宾华人]]<ref>{{cite book |last=Rottman |first=Gordon |title=The Cabanatuan Prison Raid -?The Philippines 1945 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=GzoaH7paYwIC&lpg=PA4&dq=%22Chinese%20Filipinos%22%20surrender%20Japan&pg=PA4#v=onepage&q=%22Chinese%20Filipinos%22%20surrender%20Japan&f=false |accessdate=2013-01-08 |year=2012 |publisher=Osprey Publishing |isbn=9781782004974 |page=4 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191603/http://books.google.com/books?id=GzoaH7paYwIC&lpg=PA4&dq=%22Chinese%20Filipinos%22%20surrender%20Japan&pg=PA4#v=onepage&q=%22Chinese%20Filipinos%22%20surrender%20Japan&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。他们被强令步行至[[圣费尔南多_(邦板牙)|圣费尔南多]]，这就是后世所称的“[[巴丹死亡行军|巴丹死亡行军]]”，大约5000到10000名菲律宾战俘死于途中<ref>{{cite web|url=http://home.pacbell.net/fbaldie/In_Retrospect.html|title=Bataan, Corregidor, and the Death March: In Retrospect|date=2002-10-28|first=Maj. Richard M., (U.S. Army, retired)|last=Gordon|accessdate=2007-09-27|archive-date=2008-05-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080514223319/http://home.pacbell.net/fbaldie/In_Retrospect.html|dead-url=no}}<br/>{{cite web |url=http://philippine-defenders.lib.wv.us/html/bataan.html |title=Bataan Death March |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |work=The Brooke County Public Library Foundation-ADBC Museum |publisher=Brooke County Public Library |accessdate=2013-01-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130704211901/http://philippine-defenders.lib.wv.us/html/bataan.html |archive-date=2013-07-04 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。继续在[[科雷希多岛|科雷希多岛]]山区进行抵抗的少数参与部队随着[[科雷吉多島戰役_(1942年)|日军进攻科雷希多岛]]也彻底土崩瓦解。是年5月，美军驻菲总司令官[[喬納森·溫萊特|乔纳森·温莱特]]中将向日军投降<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.history.com/this-day-in-history/all-american-forces-in-the-philippines-surrender-unconditionally |title=All American forces in the Philippines surrender unconditionally |author= |date= |work=History.com |publisher=A&E Television Networks |accessdate=2012-07-05 |archive-date=2012-10-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121024201124/http://www.history.com/this-day-in-history/all-american-forces-in-the-philippines-surrender-unconditionally |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在降将之中，有23名西点军校毕业的菲律宾军官，日军将其中的6人处决，这里面包括了前章节所叙述的菲律宾华裔军校生文森特·林，他毕业后在美国陆军的菲律宾侦查军服役，官至中校，菲律宾自治后又在菲律宾陆军中升至准将<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dtic.mil/cgi-bin/GetTRDoc?AD=ADA100220 |title=USMA Foreign Cadet Program—A Case Study |author=Colonel Clarence E. Endy, Jr. |date=1981-05-04 |work=United States Army War College |publisher=Defense Technical Information center |accessdate=2012-09-11 |archive-date=2013-04-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130408132053/http://www.dtic.mil/cgi-bin/GetTRDoc?AD=ADA100220 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

在美国国内，菲裔起初是被禁止入伍的，这一项法案直到日本入侵菲律宾的前一日才得到修正<ref>{{cite book |title=Filipinos in America |last=Frank |first=Sarah |year=2005 |publisher=Lerner Publications |isbn=978-0-8225-4873-7 |page=37 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=9Yr-p5T54qEC&lpg=PA37&ots=Tuyv5ydKXH&dq=%22First%20Filipino%20Regiment%22&pg=PA37#v=onepage&q=%22First%20Filipino%20Regiment%22&f=false |accessdate=2009-11-12 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191758/http://books.google.com/books?id=9Yr-p5T54qEC&lpg=PA37&ots=Tuyv5ydKXH&dq=%22First%20Filipino%20Regiment%22&pg=PA37#v=onepage&q=%22First%20Filipino%20Regiment%22&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。一些菲裔在非种族隔离的部队中服役<ref>{{cite web |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=AhGgymG6luMC&pg=PA234&lpg=PA234&dq=%22A+Filipino+Rookie+In+Uncle+Sam%27s+Army%22&source=bl&ots=poyiLxAE91&sig=bUwcZJjssYfbXvryC9j6vIVZRj4&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj394an_97UAhWJx4MKHXByCOoQ6AEIKjAB#v=onepage&q=%22A%20Filipino%20Rookie%20In%20Uncle%20Sam's%20Army%22&f=false |title=A Filipino Rookie In Uncle Sam's Army |author=Doroteo V. Vite |date= |work=Asian American Studies 456 Filipinos In America Course Reader |publisher=San Francisco State University |accessdate=2009-11-12 |archive-date=2019-05-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190513025613/https://books.google.com/books?id=AhGgymG6luMC&pg=PA234&lpg=PA234&dq=%22A+Filipino+Rookie+In+Uncle+Sam%27s+Army%22&source=bl&ots=poyiLxAE91&sig=bUwcZJjssYfbXvryC9j6vIVZRj4&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwj394an_97UAhWJx4MKHXByCOoQ6AEIKjAB#v=onepage&q=%22A%20Filipino%20Rookie%20In%20Uncle%20Sam's%20Army%22&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>，其他人则编组为一个菲裔步兵营。当加入人数的不断增多达到顶点之时，军方将其一分为二，是为美国陆军第1和第2菲裔步兵团（Filipino Infantry Regiment）<ref name="CAINF">{{cite web |url=http://www.militarymuseum.org/Filipino.html |title=California's Filipino Infantry |author=Alex S. Fabros |date= |work=The California State Military Museum |publisher=California State Military Department |accessdate=2009-11-12 |archive-date=2011-06-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110613090844/http://www.militarymuseum.org/Filipino.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。这些士兵在比尔基地（Camp Beale）和奥尔德堡（Fort Ord）受训时遭受到了种族歧视，有时在外出的时候还会被误认为是日裔<ref>{{cite book |title=The Third Asiatic Invasion: Migration and Empire in Filipino America, 1898–1946 |last=Baldoz |first=Rick |authorlink= |coauthors= |year=2011 |publisher=NYU Press |location=New York |isbn=978-0-8147-9109-7 |page=214 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=qtn31sdI4j8C&lpg=PA10&dq=The%20Third%20Asiatic%20Invasion%3A%20Migration%20and%20Empire%20in%20Filipino%20America%2C%201898-1946%20(Nation%20of%20Newcomers)&pg=PA214#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2011-06-07 |archive-date=2014-01-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140104141448/http://books.google.com/books?id=qtn31sdI4j8C&lpg=PA10&dq=The%20Third%20Asiatic%20Invasion%3A%20Migration%20and%20Empire%20in%20Filipino%20America%2C%201898-1946%20(Nation%20of%20Newcomers)&pg=PA214#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。尽管如此，菲裔部队就像日裔的第442步兵团一样战功彪炳，虽然他们的功绩并不像442团一样完善记录下来，广为人知<ref name="DEOMI" /><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Nakano |first1=Satoshi |year=2004 |title=The Filipino World War II veterans equity movement and the Filipino American community |journal=Seventh Annual International Philippine Studies |publisher=Center for Pacific And American Studies |url=http://www.cpas.c.u-tokyo.ac.jp/pub/PAS6_Nakano_133-58.pdf |accessdate=2011-03-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722080219/http://www.cpas.c.u-tokyo.ac.jp/pub/PAS6_Nakano_133-58.pdf |archivedate=2011-07-22 }}</ref>。在战争结束时，这两支菲裔部队的军人共得到了多达50,000份的奖章、奖励、勋章、勋表、证书、奖状和褒扬，这些荣誉来自他们在新几内亚战役和[[菲律賓戰役_(1944年至1945年)|菲律宾战役]]的出色表现<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hmdb.org/marker.asp?marker=28040 |title=The First and Second Filipino Infantry Regiments U.S. Army |author=Andrew Ruppenstien |coauthors=Manny Santos |date=2010-01-21 |work= |publisher=Historic Marker Database |accessdate=2011-05-10 |quote=Personnel won more than 50,000 decorations, awards, medals, ribbons, certificates, commendations and citations. |archive-date=2011-09-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110923152624/http://www.hmdb.org/marker.asp?marker=28040 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

美军在菲律宾投降后，仍然有小股的军人不愿投降，他们采用游击战的方式抗击驻菲日军。成员有獲釋的战俘、菲律宾平民和盟军其他部分中不愿投降的散兵游勇<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pbs.org/wgbh//amex/macarthur/sfeature/bataan_guerrilla.html |title=The Guerrilla War |author= |date= |work=MacArthur |publisher=PBS |accessdate=2009-11-12 |archive-date=2009-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090308112944/http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/amex/macarthur/sfeature/bataan_guerrilla.html |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite book |title=Us Special Warfare Units in the Pacific Theater 1941–45 |last=Rottman |first=Gordon L. |year=2005 |publisher=Osprey Publishing |isbn=978-1-84176-707-9 |pages=39–43，96 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=sMnCNdLO888C&lpg=PA41&ots=7OPS3qfLis&dq=5217th%20Reconnaissance%20Battalion&pg=PA40#v=onepage&q=5217th%20Reconnaissance%20Battalion&f=false |accessdate=2009-11-14 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191654/http://books.google.com/books?id=sMnCNdLO888C&lpg=PA41&ots=7OPS3qfLis&dq=5217th%20Reconnaissance%20Battalion&pg=PA40#v=onepage&q=5217th%20Reconnaissance%20Battalion&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。1944年，由麦克阿瑟率领的同盟国大军在雷伊泰岛战役重返菲律宾，这里面包括了裁员后的菲裔步兵单位<ref>{{cite news |title=New film depicts Filipino regiments' exploits |author=Scott Ishikawa |url=http://the.honoluluadvertiser.com/article/2001/Nov/30/ln/ln03a.html |newspaper=Honolulu Advertiser |date=2001-11-30 |accessdate=2011-04-28 |archive-date=2012-10-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121009043525/http://the.honoluluadvertiser.com/article/2001/Nov/30/ln/ln03a.html |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite book |title=Filipinos in America |last=Frank |first=Sarah |year=2005 |publisher=Lerner Publications |location=Minneapolis, Minnesota |isbn=978-0-8225-4873-7 |page=39 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=9Yr-p5T54qEC&lpg=PA37&ots=Tvtu8DiHSC&dq=%22Filipino%20Infantry%20regiment%22&pg=PA39#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2011-04-28 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191714/http://books.google.com/books?id=9Yr-p5T54qEC&lpg=PA37&ots=Tvtu8DiHSC&dq=%22Filipino%20Infantry%20regiment%22&pg=PA39#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。 同年年末，菲律宾步兵师重新组建<ref>(Nota Bene: These combat chronicles, current as of October 1948, are reproduced from The Army Almanac: A Book of Facts Concerning the Army of the United States, U.S. Government Printing Office, 1950, pp. 510–592.)</ref>。这些军人中被选派留守菲律宾者在1945年二战胜利后就地改编为菲律宾自治领陆军<ref name="CAINF"/>。在二战中，总共有约142000菲律宾人参军<ref name="FASWW2">{{cite news |title=Aging Filipinos who fought for U.S. live lonely lives waiting for promises to be kept |author=Emelyn Cruz Lat |url=http://articles.sfgate.com/1997-05-25/news/28568977_1 |newspaper=San Francisco Examiner |date=1997-05-25 |accessdate=2011-03-15 |archive-date=2012-01-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120117121620/http://articles.sfgate.com/1997-05-25/news/28568977_1 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.philippine-scouts.org/history.html |title=Post World War II Philippine Scouts |author=J. Michael Houlahan |date=2007-05-11 |work=History |publisher=Philippine Scouts Heritage Society |accessdate=2009-11-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090430073214/http://www.philippine-scouts.org/history.html |archive-date=2009-04-30 |dead-url=yes }}<br/>{{cite web |url=http://akaka.senate.gov/statements-and-speeches.cfm?method=releases.view&id=70972a30-b1fc-46d1-8390-df63eba8a217 |title=Statement on Senator Daniel K. Akaka before the Senate Veterans' Affairs committee hearing on pending legislation |author=Senator Daniel Akaka |date=1997-07-25 |work=Senator Daniel Akaka |publisher=United States Senate |accessdate=2011-03-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110117183210/http://akaka.senate.gov/statements-and-speeches.cfm?method=releases.view&id=70972a30-b1fc-46d1-8390-df63eba8a217 |archivedate=2011-01-17 }}</ref>。如果再算上游击队伍<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.va.gov/opa/publications/factsheets/fs_filipino_veterans.pdf |title=VA Benefits for Filipino Veterans |author= |date=April 2008 |work= |publisher=United States Department of Veterans Affairs |accessdate=2011-03-15 |archive-date=2010-12-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101206172841/http://www1.va.gov/opa/publications/factsheets/fs_filipino_veterans.pdf |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite web |url=http://www.archives.gov/st-louis/military-personnel/philippine-army-records.html |title=Philippine Army and Guerrilla Records |author= |date= |work=National Personnel Records Center, St. Louis |publisher=The U.S. National Archives and Records Administration |accessdate=2011-03-15 |archive-date=2010-12-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101208071847/http://archives.gov/st-louis/military-personnel/philippine-army-records.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，这个数字约为250,000<ref>{{cite book |title=Diary of the war: World War II memoirs of Lt. Col. Anastacio Campo |last=Virginia Yap Morales |first=Maria |year=2006 |publisher=Ateneo de Manila University Press |location=Quezon City |isbn=978-971-550-489-8 |page=198 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=oPPh-Of8sEwC&lpg=PP1&vq=750%2C000&pg=PA198#v=snippet&q=250000&f=false |accessdate=2011-03-15 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191722/http://books.google.com/books?id=oPPh-Of8sEwC&lpg=PP1&vq=750,000&pg=PA198#v=snippet&q=250000&f=false |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite book |title=Filipinos in the East Bay |last=Canonizado Buell |first=Evengeline |coauthors=Evelyn Luluguisen, Lillian Galedo, Eleanor Hipol Luis |year=2008 |publisher=Arcadia Publishing |isbn=978-0-7385-5832-5 |page=8 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=m4cagVAo5D0C&lpg=PA8&vq=250%2C000&pg=PA8#v=snippet&q=250,000&f=false |accessdate=2011-03-15 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191637/http://books.google.com/books?id=m4cagVAo5D0C&lpg=PA8&vq=250,000&pg=PA8#v=snippet&q=250,000&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>，甚至最多可达400,000人<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nps.gov/subjects/tellingallamericansstories/upload/AAPI-Booklet-508-1-1.pdf |title=Asian Heritage in the National Park Service Cultural Resources Programs |author= |date= |work= |publisher=National Park Service |accessdate=2011-03-15 |archive-date=2017-03-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170301175938/https://www.nps.gov/subjects/tellingallamericansstories/upload/AAPI-Booklet-508-1-1.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

{{link-en|何塞·卡鲁加斯|Jose Calugas}}中士是二战中第一位获得荣誉勋章的军人，也是所有亚裔中第三位获得该项荣誉之人<ref>{{cite book |title=Go For Broke: The Nisei Warriors of World War II Who Conquered Germany |last=Sterner |first=C. Douglas |year=2007 |publisher=American Legacy Media |location=Clearfield, Utah |isbn=978-0-9796896-1-1 |pages=134–135 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=teeObc0NHUAC&lpg=PA134&dq=Jose%20Calugas&pg=PA134#v=onepage&q=Jose%20Calugas&f=false |accessdate=2011-03-02 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191753/http://books.google.com/books?id=teeObc0NHUAC&lpg=PA134&dq=Jose%20Calugas&pg=PA134#v=onepage&q=Jose%20Calugas&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>，他在菲律宾收复后才获颁这项殊荣<ref>{{cite news |title= Jose Calugas, Medal of Honor Winnier 'Death March' Survivor |author= Carole Beers |url= http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?date=19980124&slug=2730347 |newspaper= The Seattle Times |date= 1998-01-24 |accessdate= 2011-03-02 |archive-date= 2012-09-19 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20120919223749/http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?date=19980124&slug=2730347 |dead-url= no }}</ref>。2000年，在亚裔老兵功勋的重审中，{{link-en|鲁道夫·达维拉|Rudolph B. Davila}}中尉在二战中获得的杰出服役十字勋章升格为荣誉勋章<ref>{{Cite news |title=Rudolph Davila, 85, Recipient of Highest Award for Valor |author=Richard Goldstein |newspaper=New York Times |date=2002-02-11 |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/11/us/rudolph-davila-85-recipient-of-highest-award-for-valor.html |accessdate=2011-03-02 |archive-date=2013-06-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130618184159/http://www.nytimes.com/2002/02/11/us/rudolph-davila-85-recipient-of-highest-award-for-valor.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。莱昂·潘萨朗（Leon Punsalang）中校则在几内亚战役中成为首位统领白人部队的亚裔军官<ref name="CAINF" /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.csun.edu/~sg4002/courses/417/417_lectures/417_post_war.htm |title=Geography 417 |author=Dr. Steven M. Graves |date= |work=Geography 417 |publisher=California State University, Northridge |accessdate=2011-05-18 |quote=Lt. Col. Leon Punsalang, a West Point graduate, command of the 1st Battalion marking the first time in that an Asian American commanded white troops in combat. |archive-date=2011-09-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110916081200/http://www.csun.edu/~sg4002/courses/417/417_lectures/417_post_war.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。 此外，两位菲裔女性古雷罗（Josefina Guerrero）和芬奇（Florence Finch）因在战争中帮助盟军战俘而获颁[[總統自由勳章|总统自由勋章]]<ref name="WomenWWII" />。芬奇还在后来加入海岸警卫队女兵预备役部队<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uscg.mil/history/people/FlorenceFinchBio.asp |title=Florence Ebersole Smith Finch, USCGR (W) |author= |date=2012-05-08 |work=United States Coast Guard |publisher=United States Department of Homeland Security |accessdate=2012-07-18 |archive-date=2012-09-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120927041609/http://www.uscg.mil/history/people/FlorenceFinchBio.asp |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=====韩裔=====
{{See also|金永玉}}
[[File:Ahn_Siblings_World_War_II.jpg|thumb]]、{{Link-en|安必英|Ralph Ahn}}]]
自从美国与[[朝鲜王朝|朝鲜王朝]]于1882年签署友好通商条约之后，便开始有朝鲜人移民美国<ref name="APAT"/>，直至1910年[[日韩合并|日韩合并]]<ref name="Giudici">{{cite web |url=http://www.historylink.org/index.cfm?DisplayPage=output.cfm&file_id=3251 |title=Korean Americans in King County |author=Carey Giudici |date=2001-05-31 |work=Cyberpedia Library |publisher=HistoryLink.org |accessdate=2009-11-20 |archive-date=2010-06-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100620113948/http://historylink.org/index.cfm?DisplayPage=output.cfm&file_id=3251 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。受[[日韩合并|日韩合并]]的影响，在美国参战初期，韩裔也被当成“敌国之人”对待<ref name="Giudici"/>，直至1943年，韩裔才从此称呼中得到豁免<ref>{{cite news |title= Korean American History |author= NAKA |url= http://www.naka.org/resources/history.asp |newspaper= NAKA |date= 10–16 January 2003 |accessdate= 2011-03-02 |archive-date= 2011-06-02 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20110602085824/http://www.naka.org/resources/history.asp |dead-url= no }}<br/>{{cite book |title= The Koreas |last= Armstrong |first= Charles K. |year= 2007 |publisher= CRC Press |location= New York, New York |isbn= 978-0-415-94853-1 |page= 104 |url= http://books.google.com/books?id=_mh4Qv4lAkQC&lpg=PT116&ots=sNpl1eOQMv&dq=Military%20Order%20No.%2045%20Korean%20Americans&pg=PT116#v=onepage&q=Military%20Order%20No.%2045%20Korean%20Americans&f=false |accessdate= 2011-03-02 |archive-date= 2014-06-27 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191619/http://books.google.com/books?id=_mh4Qv4lAkQC&lpg=PT116&ots=sNpl1eOQMv&dq=Military%20Order%20No.%2045%20Korean%20Americans&pg=PT116#v=onepage&q=Military%20Order%20No.%2045%20Korean%20Americans&f=false |dead-url= no }}</ref>。在二战中，大约有100名韩裔人士加入美国陆军<ref name="KASWW2">{{cite web |url=http://www.asianresearch.org/articles/1633.html |title=The Korean Americans in the War of Independence |author=Kim Young Sik, Ph.D. |date=2003-11-09 |work=East Asia |publisher=Association for Asia Research |accessdate=2009-11-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100918010308/http://asianresearch.org/articles/1633.html |archive-date=2010-09-18 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>，他们中的一部分人从事翻译工作<ref>{{cite book |title=Koreans in America |last=Taus-Bolstad |first=Stacy |year=2005 |publisher=Lerner Publications |isbn=978-0-8225-4874-4 |page=45 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=g6Tw_NPEe58C&lpg=PA45&ots=NK8l58CyDY&dq=%22Korean%20americans%22%20World%20War%20II&pg=PA45#v=onepage&q=%22Korean%20americans%22%20World%20War%20II&f=false |accessdate=2009-11-20 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191704/http://books.google.com/books?id=g6Tw_NPEe58C&lpg=PA45&ots=NK8l58CyDY&dq=%22Korean%20americans%22%20World%20War%20II&pg=PA45#v=onepage&q=%22Korean%20americans%22%20World%20War%20II&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。还有超过100人选择在[[洛杉矶|洛杉矶]]加入加州国民警卫队，由他们所组成的单位后来称作“猛虎軍”（Tiger Brigade，{{lang|ko|맹호군}}）<ref>{{cite book |last=Kim |first=Kathrine Yungmee |title=Los Angeles's Koreatown |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=lgaL4QsFHDUC&lpg=PA55&ots=oB_UArbQv1&dq=Korean%20%22Tiger%20Brigade%22%20%22California%20National%20Guard%22&pg=PA55#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2013-02-05 |year=2011 |publisher=Arcadia Publishing |isbn=9780738575520 |page=55 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191525/http://books.google.com/books?id=lgaL4QsFHDUC&lpg=PA55&ots=oB_UArbQv1&dq=Korean%20%22Tiger%20Brigade%22%20%22California%20National%20Guard%22&pg=PA55#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite book |last=Wilmoth |first=Janet M. |last2=London |first2=Andrew S. |title=Life Course Perspectives on Military Service |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=-TdqEVEtXLQC&lpg=PA85&ots=O2198U0pjL&dq=Racism%20%22Asian%22%20%22United%20States%20Military%22%20%22Korean%20War%22&pg=PA85#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2013-02-05 |year=2013 |publisher=Routledge |isbn=9780415879415 |page=85 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191605/http://books.google.com/books?id=-TdqEVEtXLQC&lpg=PA85&ots=O2198U0pjL&dq=Racism%20%22Asian%22%20%22United%20States%20Military%22%20%22Korean%20War%22&pg=PA85#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite book |last=Ryang |first=Sonia |last2=Lie |first2=John |title=Diaspora Without Homeland: Being Korean in Japan |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=78537bNL7VIC&lpg=PA161&ots=0ayyoFfM-u&dq=Korean%20%22Tiger%20Brigade%22%20%22California%20National%20Guard%22&pg=PA161#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2013-02-05 |year=2009 |publisher=University of California Press |isbn=9780520098633 |page=161 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191749/http://books.google.com/books?id=78537bNL7VIC&lpg=PA161&ots=0ayyoFfM-u&dq=Korean%20%22Tiger%20Brigade%22%20%22California%20National%20Guard%22&pg=PA161#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite web |url=http://www.militarymuseum.org/KoreanRegiment.html |title=California Korean Reserve |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |work=California State Military Museum |publisher=California State Military Department |accessdate=2013-02-05 |archive-date=2011-02-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110206082313/http://militarymuseum.org/KoreanRegiment.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。后来升至[[上校|上校]]的[[金永玉|金永玉]]是二战韩裔军人中的知名人士之一。他最初曾在选兵时被美国陆军拒绝，入伍后在工兵部队服役直至1943年經选拔成为军官，他大部分时间都在日裔第442团服役<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goforbroke.org/learn/archives/oral_histories_archives.php |title=Oral History |author= |date= |work=Oral History |publisher=Go For Broke National Education Center |accessdate=2009-11-20 |archive-date=2016-03-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160312192703/http://www.goforbroke.org/learn/archives/oral_histories_archives.php |dead-url=no }}</ref>。金永玉在[[鹅卵石行动|安济奥之战]]中获得了杰出服役十字勋章<ref name="GKK">{{cite news |title=Soldier embodied bravery of 100th Battalion vets |author=Gregg K. Kakesako |newspaper=Honolulu Star Bulletin |date=2006-01-04 |url=http://archives.starbulletin.com/2006/01/04/news/story09.html |accessdate=2009-11-20 |archive-date=2010-08-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100808080752/http://archives.starbulletin.com/2006/01/04/news/story09.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，是二战期间唯一获此殊荣的韩裔美国人<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.homeofheroes.com/moh/nisei/index5_anzio.html |title=Anzio and the Road to Rome |author=C. Douglas Sterner |date= |work= |publisher=HomeOfHeroes.com |accessdate=2009-11-20 |archive-date=2009-11-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091102203347/http://www.homeofheroes.com/moh/nisei/index5_anzio.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，他在先前的战役中还获得了[[银星勋章|银星勋章]]和[[紫心勋章|紫心勋章]]<ref name="GKK"/>。还有位名叫{{link-en|弗雷德·吴|Fred Ohr}}（Fred Ohr）的韩裔军人是二战时期唯一一名韩裔[[王牌飞行员|王牌飞行员]]<ref name="FOhr10NOV11">{{cite news |title=Veterans Day: Korean-American defied the odds to become ace fighter pilot |author=Margaret Downing |url=http://www.wifr.com/home/headlines/Stateline-Spotlight--231498181.html |newspaper=Stateline News |date=2011-11-10 |accessdate=2012-03-08 |archive-date=2014-03-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140331181512/http://www.wifr.com/home/headlines/Stateline-Spotlight--231498181.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。他在战斗中一共击落过6架敌机，因战功升任地中海战区{{Link-en|美國空軍第52戰鬥機聯隊|52d Fighter Wing|第52战斗机大隊}}{{Link-en|美國空軍第2戰鬥機中隊|2d Fighter Squadron|第2中队}}的中隊長<ref name="AJNov2008">{{cite journal |last1=Bledsoe |first1=Larry W. |last2= |first2= |year=2008 |title=Fighter Pilots Lived Their Dreams |journal=Airport Journal |volume= |issue= |pages= |publisher=Hansen Airport Journals LLC |doi= |url=http://airportjournals.com/fighter-pilots-lived-their-dreams/ |accessdate=2012-03-08 |archive-date=2015-04-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150403082617/http://airportjournals.com/fighter-pilots-lived-their-dreams/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。直至目前为止，他依然是唯一一名获得王牌飞行员称号的韩裔美国人<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.museumofflight.org/press/world-war-ii-american-fighter-aces-museum |title=World War II American Fighter Aces at Museum |author= |date=2009-07-01 |work= |publisher=The Museum of Flight |accessdate=2012-03-08 |quote=The Museum will host a panel of three fighter pilots: Capt. Fred Ohr, who is the only American ace of Korean ancestry, and had six aerial victories and 17 ground victories; Lt. Col. Richard W. Asbury, who participated in 240 combat missions spanning three wars; and Lt. Col. Stan Richardson, who flew P-38s and P-51s in the European Theater during World War II, and participated in the D-Day Invasion. |archive-date=2010-12-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101228180959/http://www.museumofflight.org/press/world-war-ii-american-fighter-aces-museum |dead-url=no }}</ref>。弗雷德在参与的军事行动中获得了诸多荣誉，包括了兩枚銀星勳章<ref name="FOhr10NOV11" />。

