=====二战之后=====
{{See also|同盟国军事占领德国|同盟国军事占领日本}}
[[日本投降|日本投降]]之后，第二次世界大战结束，美国开始了裁军工作，多达数百万的军人退伍返乡，第442步兵团的战士们也在其列。1946年，杜鲁门总统检阅了第442步兵团，并第七次授予该团总统部队嘉奖称号。他们随后复员，但一年后又召回重组，改编为陆军预备役部队<ref>{{cite web | title = 100th Battalion, 442nd Infantry | publisher = GlobalSecurity.org | url = http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/agency/army/100-442in.htm | date = 2005-05-23 | accessdate = 2008-09-27 | archive-date = 2008-09-11 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080911011150/http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/agency/army/100-442in.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref>。同年，杜鲁门签署了{{link-en|废除法案|Rescission Act of 1946}} ，取消了承诺给予菲律宾自治领、游击队老兵的福利待遇<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pbs.org/wgbh//amex/macarthur/sfeature/bataan_filipino.html |title=The Filipino Veterans Movement |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |year=1996 |work=WGBH Educational Foundation |publisher=Public Broadcasting Service |accessdate=2013-02-05 |archive-date=2013-03-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130301232618/http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/amex/macarthur/sfeature/bataan_filipino.html |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite news |title=Ron Paul to speak to Filipino WWII veterans at rally |author=Keith Rogers |url=https://www.reviewjournal.com/news/ron-paul-to-speak-to-filipino-wwii-veterans-at-rally/ |newspaper=Las Vegas Review-Journal |date=2013-02-03 |accessdate=2013-02-05 |archive-date=2019-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190222033438/https://www.reviewjournal.com/news/ron-paul-to-speak-to-filipino-wwii-veterans-at-rally/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。 经过菲律宾政府的同意，50000名菲律宾侦查军的士兵经美国国会许可保持建制<ref name="JBW">{{cite book |title=Maneuver and Firepower |last=Wilson |first=John B. |coauthors=Jeffrey J. Clarke |year=1998 |publisher=Center of Military History, United States Army |location=Washington D.C. |isbn= |page=212 |url=http://www.history.army.mil/html/books/060/60-14-1/cmhPub_60-14-1.pdf |accessdate=2009-11-22 |quote=As the nation demobilized, Congress approved, with the consent of the Philippine government, the maintenance of 50,000 Philippine Scouts (PS) as occupation forces for Japan. On 6 April 1946 Maj. Gen. Louis E. Hibbs, who had commanded the 63d Infantry Division during the war, reorganized the Philippine Division, which had surrendered on Bataan in 1942, as the 12th Infantry Division (PS). Unlike its predecessor, the 12th's enlisted personnel were exclusively Philippine Scouts.<br/>The War Department proposed to organize a second Philippine Scout division, the 14th, but never did so. After a short period President Harry S. Truman decided to disband all Philippine Scout units, determining that they were not needed for duty in Japan. The United States could not afford them, and he felt the Republic of the Philippines, a sovereign nation, should not furnish mercenaries for the United States. Therefore, the Far East Command inactivated the 12th Infantry Division (PS) in 1947 and eventually inactivated or disbanded all Philippine Scout units. |archive-date=2014-03-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140301211444/http://www.history.army.mil/html/books/060/60-14-1/cmhPub_60-14-1.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>作为菲律宾步兵师的一部分参与了[[琉球列島美國軍政府|占领琉球]]的任务直到1947年解散<ref>{{cite book |title=In the Philippines and Okinawa: a memoir, 1945–1948 |last=Triplet |first=William S. |coauthors=Robert H. Ferrell |year=2001 |publisher=University of Missouri Press |isbn=978-0-8262-1335-8 |pages=299 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=h5x7wobGXI0C&dq=new+philippine+scouts+ryukyu&source=gbs_navlinks_s |accessdate=2009-11-14 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191515/http://books.google.com/books?id=h5x7wobGXI0C&dq=new+philippine+scouts+ryukyu&source=gbs_navlinks_s |dead-url=no }}</ref>，旋即还被杜鲁门视为[[雇佣兵|雇佣兵]]组织<ref name="JBW"/>。1948年，杜鲁门签署了9981号行政命令，废除了军中的种族隔离制度<ref>{{cite book |title=Harry and Ike: The Partnership That Remade the Postwar World |last=Neal |first=Steve |authorlink= |year=2002 |publisher=Simon and Schuster |location= |isbn=9780743223744 |page=103 |accessdate=2012-08-19 |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=AbcQpkhgvFIC&lpg=PA103&ots=Abj9rkHOqX&dq=desegregation%20Truman%20military%20Executive%20Order%209981&pg=PA103#v=onepage&q=desegregation%20Truman%20military%20Executive%20Order%209981&f=false |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191614/http://books.google.com/books?id=AbcQpkhgvFIC&lpg=PA103&ots=Abj9rkHOqX&dq=desegregation%20Truman%20military%20Executive%20Order%209981&pg=PA103#v=onepage&q=desegregation%20Truman%20military%20Executive%20Order%209981&f=false |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite web |url=http://www.trumanlibrary.org/anniversaries/desegblurb.htm |title=This Day in Truman History: July 26, 1948 |author= |date= |work=Harry S. Truman Library and Museum |publisher=National Archives and Records Administration |accessdate=2012-08-19 |archive-date=2013-04-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130413020623/http://www.trumanlibrary.org/anniversaries/desegblurb.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=====韓戰=====
{{See also|韓戰|呂超然}}
[[File:Hiroshi_Miyamura_and_Eisenhowser.jpg|thumb]]总统授予宫村[[上士|上士]][[荣誉勋章|荣誉勋章]]]]
1950年，[[朝鲜战争|朝鲜战争]]爆发。1951年，多数亚裔军事单位因军中种族隔离制度的废除而解散，士兵重新分配至其他部队；不过也有少数像第100步兵营、第442步兵团和第5步兵团战斗单位继续维持传统，大宗兵力仍由亚裔军人组成<ref name="NJ">{{cite web |url=http://www.state.nj.us/military//korea/factsheets/asian.html |title=Asian-Americans i the United States Military during the Korean War |author= |date= |work= |publisher=State of New Jersey |accessdate=2011-02-14 |archive-date=2011-06-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110628182435/http://www.state.nj.us/military//korea/factsheets/asian.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。朝鲜战争中亚裔军人的具体参战人数目前尚无定论<ref name="NJ" /><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Boose Jr. |first1=Donald W. |year=2002 |title=Hills of Sacrifice: The 5th RCT in Korea |journal=Korean Studies |volume=26 |issue=2 |pages=316–318 |publisher= |url=http://www.questia.com/googleScholar.qst;jsessionid=6631E56707A84E9DCC73B4A321FCCF89.inst1_3a?docId=5002106846 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110628213824/http://www.questia.com/googleScholar.qst;jsessionid=6631E56707A84E9DCC73B4A321FCCF89.inst1_3a?docId=5002106846 |archivedate=2011-06-28 |accessdate=2011-02-14 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，阵亡者则一共有241人<ref name="DMDC2009">{{cite web |url=https://www.dmdc.osd.mil/dcas/pages/Documents/RACE-OMB-WC.pdf |title=Active Duty Military Deaths – Race/Ethnicity Summary |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=2009-07-25 |work=Defense Manpower Data Center |publisher=United States Department of Defense |accessdate=2013-01-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130222053716/https://www.dmdc.osd.mil/dcas/pages/Documents/RACE-OMB-WC.pdf |archive-date=2013-02-22 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

在第7步兵团服役的{{link-en|浩·H·宫村|Hiroshi H. Miyamura|浩·宮村}}是朝鲜战争中唯一获得荣誉勋章的亚裔军人<ref>{{cite web |title=History: Korean War |url=http://www.cabq.gov/parksandrecreation/parks/veterans-memorial-park/history/koreanwar |author=Lou Hoffman |date= |work=The New Mexico Veterans' Memorial, Museum, & Conference Center |publisher=City of Albuquerque |accessdate=2013-08-07 |archive-date=2013-05-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130527002041/http://www.cabq.gov/parksandrecreation/parks/veterans-memorial-park/history/koreanwar |dead-url=no }}</ref>。决定授予其这项殊荣的时候，宫村尚在朝鲜半島做战俘，为避免其因此遭受迫害，此事在当时列为[[国家机密|最高机密]]。直至1953年宫村获释回国后，才由艾森豪威尔总统正式授予荣誉勋章<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fas.org/sgp/congress/2001/s032201.html |title=America's First Top Secret Hero |author=United States Congress |date=2001-03-22 |work=Congressional Record |publisher= |accessdate=2011-02-14 |archive-date=2011-06-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110628192856/http://www.fas.org/sgp/congress/2001/s032201.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。美籍華裔李氏三兄弟，[[呂超然|呂超然]]（Kurt Chew-Een Lee，首位美籍華裔海軍陸戰隊常備役军官）、呂超民（Chew-Mon Lee，陆军步兵军官、後於[[台灣|台灣]]任美國駐[[中華民國|中華民國]][[上校|上校]][[駐外武官|武官]]）、呂超凡（音譯；Chew-Fan Lee，陆军医官）分别在战争中获得了[[海軍十字勳章|海军十字勋章]]、傑出服役十字勋章、[[銅星勳章|铜星勋章]]等殊荣<ref>{{cite book |last=Tom |first=Lawrence |last2=Tom |first2=Brian |author3=Chinese American Museum of Northern California |title=Sacramento's Chinatown |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=SOXth7IZYrYC&lpg=PA95&ots=ffBdYcaLAi&dq=Chew-Mon%20Lee%20Distinguished%20Service%20Cross&pg=PA95#v=onepage&q=Chew-Mon%20Lee%20Distinguished%20Service%20Cross&f=false |accessdate= |year=2010 |publisher=Arcadia Publishing |isbn=9780738580661 |page=95 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191622/http://books.google.com/books?id=SOXth7IZYrYC&lpg=PA95&ots=ffBdYcaLAi&dq=Chew-Mon%20Lee%20Distinguished%20Service%20Cross&pg=PA95#v=onepage&q=Chew-Mon%20Lee%20Distinguished%20Service%20Cross&f=false |dead-url=no }}<br>{{cite news |title=A Short History About Chinese American Military Veterans |author=Philip Chin |url=http://www.asianweek.com/2011/10/17/a-short-history-about-chinese-american-military-veterans/ |newspaper=Asian Week |date=2011-10-17 |accessdate=2013-02-05 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130122004308/http://www.asianweek.com/2011/10/17/a-short-history-about-chinese-american-military-veterans/ |archivedate=2013-01-22 }}<br>{{cite book |last=Drury |first=Bob |last2=Clavin |first2=Tom |last3=Drury |first3=Tom |title=The Last Stand of Fox Company: A True Story of U.S. Marines in Combat |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=TOftPVDRtIcC&lpg=PA256&ots=B_Hj0FZSu2&dq=Chew-Fan%20Lee%20Bronze%20Star%20Medal&pg=PA256#v=onepage&q=Chew-Fan%20Lee%20Bronze%20Star%20Medal&f=false |accessdate=2013-02-05 |year=2009 |publisher=Grove Press |isbn=9780802144515 |page=256 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191703/http://books.google.com/books?id=TOftPVDRtIcC&lpg=PA256&ots=B_Hj0FZSu2&dq=Chew-Fan%20Lee%20Bronze%20Star%20Medal&pg=PA256#v=onepage&q=Chew-Fan%20Lee%20Bronze%20Star%20Medal&f=false |dead-url=no }}<br>{{cite web |url=http://valor.militarytimes.com/recipient.php?recipientid=7318 |title=Chew-Mon Lee |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |work=Military Times Hall of Valor |publisher=Gannett Government Media Corporation |accessdate=2013-02-05 }}<br>{{cite web |url=http://www.smithsonianchannel.com/shows/uncommon-courage-breakout-at-chosin/0/136060 |title=Uncommon Courage: Breakout at Chosin |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |year=2010 |work=Smithsonian Channel |publisher=Smithsonian Institute |accessdate=2013-02-05 |archive-date=2015-01-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150117015404/http://www.smithsonianchannel.com/shows/uncommon-courage-breakout-at-chosin/0/136060 |dead-url=no }}<br>{{cite web |url=http://valor.militarytimes.com/recipient.php?recipientid=5719 |title=Kurt Chew-Een Lee |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |work=Military Times Hall of Valor |publisher=Gannett Government Media Corporation |accessdate=2013-02-05 }}</ref>。上文提到的韩裔二战參戰軍官金永玉在朝鲜战争爆发后重新入伍，升任少校，并成为第31步兵团的第一位少数族裔指揮官<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goforbroke.org/learn/archives/oral_histories_video_public.php?publicclip=047A01 |title=Colonel Young Oak Kim (U.S. Army Ret.), 86; Decorated US WWII and Korean War Veteran |author=Mary Graybill |date= |work=Press releases |publisher=Go For Broke National Education Center |accessdate=2009-12-09 |archive-date=2016-03-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160319211639/http://www.goforbroke.org/learn/archives/oral_histories_video_public.php?publicclip=047A01 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。1927年入伍的二战军官沃尔特·塚本（Walter Tsukamoto）于1950年升任中校，是当时亚裔陆军军法官中军衔最高之人。他在第10军担任军法官，在朝鲜战争期间获得了两枚铜星勋章<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Borch III |first1=Fred L. |year=2011 |title=Colonel Walter T. Tsukamoto:  No Judge Advocate Loved America or the Army More |journal=The Army Lawyer |pages=1–5 |publisher=Judge Advocate General's Legal Center and School |issn=0364-1287 |url=http://www.loc.gov/rr/frd/Military_Law/pdf/05-2011.pdf |accessdate=2013-02-25 |archive-date=2014-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222045904/http://www.loc.gov/rr/frd/Military_Law/pdf/05-2011.pdf |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite web |url=http://www.javadc.org/tsukamoto.htm |title=Colonel Walter Takeo Tsukamoto |last1=Kobayashi |first1=Doris Tsukamoto |last2=Kobayashi |first2=Charles |last3=Ashizawa |first3=Laura Kobayashi |date=2002-06-15 |publisher=Japanese American Veterans Association |accessdate=2013-02-25 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304085914/http://www.javadc.org/tsukamoto.htm |dead-url=no }}<br/>{{cite web |url=http://www.afjag.af.mil/News/Article-Display/Article/443197/remembering-a-japanese-american-judge-advocate-colonel-walter-tsukamoto/ |title=Remembering a Japanese-American Judge Advocate: Colonel Walter Tsukamoto |last1=Hirohata |first1=Derek K. |date=2011-05-12 |work=The Judge Advocate General's Corps |publisher=United States Air Force |accessdate=2013-02-25 |archive-date=2016-12-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161222180910/http://www.afjag.af.mil/News/Article-Display/Article/443197/remembering-a-japanese-american-judge-advocate-colonel-walter-tsukamoto |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

=====越南战争=====
{{See also|越南战争|泰瑞·河村}}
[[File:Terry_T_Kawamura.jpg|thumb]]下士於陣亡後追授荣誉勋章]]
越战期间，有35,000名亚裔军人派驻[[越南共和国|南越]]<ref name="AWDEC1998">{{cite news |title=The Wounds of War-And Racism |author=Janet Dang |url=https://www.vietnam.ttu.edu/resources/indochina_chronology/pdfs/9804.pdf |newspaper=AsianWeek |date=3–9 December 1998 |accessdate=2011-03-01 |archive-date=2011-02-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110204154252/http://www.vietnam.ttu.edu/resources/indochina_chronology/pdfs/9804.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>，他们均在完全未實施种族分離的部队中服役<ref name="DEOMI" />。在这场战争中有三位追授荣誉勋章的亚裔军人，其中包括{{link-en|羅德尼·矢野|Rodney J. T. Yano}}，他是目前为止最后一位獲贈荣誉勋章的亚裔军人。此外还有[[泰瑞·河村|泰瑞·河村]]下士和{{link-en|埃尔梅林多·史密斯|Elmelindo Rodrigues Smith}}下士。亚裔军人除了在常规军中服役外，陆军还组织了一个叫做“夏威夷之队”（Team Hawaii）的特种部队，由华裔、菲裔、日裔和美洲原住民[[美國陸軍遊騎兵|游骑兵]]组成。他们的任务是假扮越南人进行大范围侦查<ref name="Zhan1999">{{cite book |editor1-first=Lin |editor1-last=Zhan |last=Zhan |first=Lin |chapter=Culture, Health, and Practices |title=Asian Americans: Vulnerable Populations, Model Interventions, and Clarifying Agendas |series=Other Nursing Titles of Interest Series |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=SDymq2IqZBMC&lpg=PA24&vq=Military&pg=PA20#v=snippet&q=Military&f=false |accessdate=2013-02-09 |year=2003 |publisher=Jones & Bartlett Learning |isbn=9780763722418 |page=20 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191719/http://books.google.com/books?id=SDymq2IqZBMC&lpg=PA24&vq=Military&pg=PA20#v=snippet&q=Military&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。种族歧视的氛围仍然伴随着亚裔军人，他们的忠诚度仍然面臨怀疑<ref name="AWDEC1998"/>。在新兵训练中，有时將他们描述为和越共相似的人<ref>{{cite book |last=Whelchel |first=Toshio |title=From Pearl Harbor to Saigon: Japanese American Soldiers and the Vietnam War |series=The Haymarket series |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=i2pjqLLmB1wC&lpg=PA104&vq=%22and%20said%2C%20This%20is%20what%20the%20Viet%20Cong%20looks%20like%2C%20with%20slanted%20eyes.%20This%20is%20what%20a%20gook%20looks%20like%2C%22&pg=PA104#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2013-02-09 |year=1999 |publisher=Verso Books |isbn=9781859848593 |page=104 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191741/http://books.google.com/books?id=i2pjqLLmB1wC&lpg=PA104&vq=%22and%20said,%20This%20is%20what%20the%20Viet%20Cong%20looks%20like,%20with%20slanted%20eyes.%20This%20is%20what%20a%20gook%20looks%20like,%22&pg=PA104#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>，有时则直接被误认，这种情形甚至曾导致亚裔军人在實戰中遭到{{Link-en|友军誤擊|friendly fire}}<ref>{{cite book |editor1-first=Lin |editor1-last=Zhan |last=Zhan |first=Lin |chapter=Culture, Health, and Practices |title=Asian Americans: Vulnerable Populations, Model Interventions, and Clarifying Agendas |series=Other Nursing Titles of Interest Series |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=SDymq2IqZBMC&lpg=PA24&vq=Military&pg=PA26#v=snippet&q=Military&f=false |accessdate=2013-02-09 |year=2003 |publisher=Jones & Bartlett Learning |isbn=9780763722418 |page=26 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191625/http://books.google.com/books?id=SDymq2IqZBMC&lpg=PA24&vq=Military&pg=PA26#v=snippet&q=Military&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>和亚裔伤兵救治延误的情况<ref>{{cite news |title=Racism against Asians persists in military |agency=Associated Press |url=http://www.telegram.com/article/20120219/NEWS/120219555/1052 |newspaper=Worcester Telegram & Gazette |date=2012-02-19 |accessdate=2013-02-05 |archive-date=2014-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222153238/http://www.telegram.com/article/20120219/NEWS/120219555/1052 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。另一方面，越共重点打击亚裔军人，时而悬赏购买亚裔军人的性命<ref name="Zhan1999"/>。与人数比例相应，亚裔军人在越战美军中所有种族里伤亡最小<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.deanza.edu/faculty/swensson/essays_mikekelley_myths.html |title=Myths & Misconceptions: Vietnam War Folklore |author=Michael Kelley |date=July 1998 |work=The Vietnam Conflict |publisher=De Anza College |accessdate=2011-03-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719183334/http://www.deanza.edu/faculty/swensson/essays_mikekelley_myths.html |archive-date=2011-07-19 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>，共139人战死沙场<ref name="DMDC2009" /><ref name="CRS Casualties">{{cite web |url=http://www.dtic.mil/dtic/tr/fulltext/u2/a458312.pdf |title=American War and Military Operations Casualties: Lists and Statistics |author=Hannah Fischer |date=2005-07-13 |work=Navy Department Library |publisher=United States Navy |accessdate=2011-03-14 |archive-date=2017-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170222104022/http://www.dtic.mil/dtic/tr/fulltext/u2/a458312.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

海军方面针对菲裔士兵的职业限制在1973年得到了改变<ref>{{cite news |first=Ramon |last=Farolan |title=From Stewards to Admirals: Filipinos in the U.S. Navy |url=https://www.history.navy.mil/research/library/online-reading-room/title-list-alphabetically/f/filipinos-in-the-united-states-navy.html |newspaper=Asian Journal |publisher= |date=2003-07-21 |accessdate=2009-09-02 |archive-date=2006-08-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060820202543/http://www.history.navy.mil/library/online/filipinos.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。经过国会对海军内部人权问题进行调查后，废除了该限制，所有职业均对菲裔开放<ref>{{cite book |last=Wilmoth |first=Janet M. |last2=London |first2=Andrew S. |title=Life Course Perspectives on Military Service |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=-TdqEVEtXLQC&lpg=PA85&ots=O2198U0pjL&dq=Racism%20%22Asian%22%20%22United%20States%20Military%22%20%22Korean%20War%22&pg=PA85#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=2013-02-07 |year=2013 |publisher=Routledge |isbn=9780415879415 |page=85 |archive-date=2014-06-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627191605/http://books.google.com/books?id=-TdqEVEtXLQC&lpg=PA85&ots=O2198U0pjL&dq=Racism%20%22Asian%22%20%22United%20States%20Military%22%20%22Korean%20War%22&pg=PA85#v=onepage&q&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

在美军之外，还有一些当时或后来加入美国国籍的其他族群曾在越战中给美军提供了一定协助。这里面包括了[[苗族|苗族]]、[[佬族|佬族]]，他们站在美国一方参与了[[寮國內戰|老挝内战]]；还有加入[[南越政府軍|南越政府軍]]作战的越裔美国人和那些给予美军帮助的越南山地族群。<ref>{{cite book | url = http://www.history.army.mil/BOOKS/Vietnam/90-23/90-23C.htm | title = History of Special Forces in Vietnam, 1961–1971 | publisher = United States Army Center of Military History | first = Francis John | last = Kelly | origyear = 1973 | year = 1989 | location = Washington, D.C. | id = CMH Pub 90-23 | pages = 6–7 | access-date = 2014-02-15 | archive-date = 2014-02-12 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140212151656/http://www.history.army.mil/books/Vietnam/90-23/90-23C.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref>

